title: spinach balls
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Drop onto cookie sheet, freeze and store in plastic bags.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and orange rind and beat until fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Spread with orange glaze while still warm.

title: stir-n-roll pie crust
directions: Work one egg and a tablespoon of sugar to as much flour as will
make
a
stiff paste, roll it as thin as a dollar and cut it into
small
round
or
square
pieces.
Drop into hot grease, when
they
rise to the surface and turn over they are done.
Take them out and drain on paper towels.

title: orange mint tea
directions: Boil water and sugar; pour over mint tea leaves.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add frozen lemonade and orange juice.
Add 3 quarts water to 1 quart of this concentrate.

title: marshmallow and fruit salad
directions: Drain and cut pineapple or leave in chunks.
Cut grapes in half or can be left whole.
Mix softened cream cheese with 3 tablespoons of the pineapple juice.
I usually add a teaspoon of sugar.
Whip the whipping cream in another bowl, adding a teaspoon of sugar.
Mix cream cheese and whipping cream together carefully. Fold in all the fruit.
Can be served immediately, but letting it refrigerate a while or even overnight will blend the flavors a little bit.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix crumbs and seasonings.
Add celery and onion.
Add beaten eggs with broth and mix well.
Add chopped boiled eggs (more seasoning if desired).
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed lightly. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.
(Mixture needs to be moist before baking.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, soup and cheese together thoroughly.
Pour part of melted butter from casserole dish and mix this in.
Put in casserole dish (I use 9 x 12-inch).
Before baking, put cornflakes or potato chips on top.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Casserole may be made beforehand except for topping and refrigerated.
Add topping when ready to bake.

title: garlic salad(great for large groups.)
directions: Break up lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Crush or mince garlic. Add garlic and dry spices to lettuce.
Toss.
Add lemon juice and toss.
Right before serving, add Parmesan cheese and oil, tossing!

title: hot turkey pie
directions: Combine turkey, celery, green pepper, onion, pecans, pepper, salt, lemon juice, mayonnaise and soup.
Spoon into pie shell. Sprinkle cheese and parsley over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, reserve 1 tablespoon pecans to sprinkle over top of pie before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine cheese, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, egg yolks, mustard, paprika, and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; gently fold into cheese mixture.
Shape mixture into small balls about one inch in diameter.
Roll in additional bread crumbs.

title: peanut butter candy cookies
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and oleo to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute (no more).
Add peanut butter, cereal and vanilla.
Mix together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet or waxed paper.
More like candy.

title: great grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Have
all
ingredients
warm
and
soft.
I
work
the ingredients
in
a
pan over hot water.
There is no liquid in the recipe and is perfect for keeping a long time.
"The older they get, the
better they are." Mix in order given.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture and drop by teaspoonfuls or larger size onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix Dream Whip and milk first, then mix sugar and cream cheese. Combine both; mix well.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Top with the cherry pie filling.
Chill 3 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain. Combine with cream of mushroom soup in a 13 x 9-inch glass casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cheese, then Tater Tots, then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Best when served hot.
Great for covered dish dinners.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs until blended.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add with milk to eggs.
Beat smooth.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Pour into greased 9-inch skillet with ovenproof handle.
Bake on bottom shelf for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Prick shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Drizzle with lemon juice; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Fill with fruit.
Cut in wedges.
Top with dollop of dairy sour cream (may add brown sugar and cinnamon).
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush in food processor Oreo cookies.
Cream the cheese, sugar and butter together.
Whip it up and then stir in cool whip.
Add cream cheese mixture and stir all together.
Layer in a bowl - cookies first, then cheese mixture, cookies, cheese, etc.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding; let thicken.
Grind cookies.
Soften cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar to cream cheese mix.
When pudding is thick, add to cream cheese mix.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Stir until mixture is creamy.
Using a plastic flowerpot, put lid to Cool Whip in the bottom of pot.
Start with cookies and layer them and pudding mixture, starting and ending with cookies.
Add gummy worms as you layer.
Place silk flowers, with plastic stem, to the finished layered pot.

title: green apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Mix well. Bake in lightly greased and floured pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: To make sauce:
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg; cook 5 minutes; add butter.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Pour yeast into hot water and set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, buttermilk, oil and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into biscuits or flour top of dough and shape with large spoon.
Place on lightly greased baking pan. Lightly oil or butter top.
Bake at 450° until golden, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Recipe can be cut into half for smaller yield.

title: golden pear salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; spoon into pear halves.
Arrange on lettuce.

title: edwards' virginia ham fantastics(this is a family favorite for holidays!)
directions: Line a 13 x 11-inch pan with foil that has been lightly greased.
Place rolls that have been filled with ample ham slices and Swiss cheese (size of quarter) on the foil-lined pan.
Place rolls very close together.
Spoon the following sauce over top of rolls.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Set saucepan in bowl of ice water and cool, then beat to spreading consistency.

title: polska kielbasa old country supper
directions: In heavy skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion to bacon drippings.
Saute over medium heat.
Add broccoli after about 15 minutes.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Slice kielbasa and place on top of vegetables.
Cover and heat 12 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: twice baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half.
Remove and discard seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until tender.
Remove squash pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
In a large mixing bowl, combine squash pulp, spinach, 1/2 cup cheese, eggs, oleo, bacon, green onion, salt and red pepper.
Fill the squash shells with squash mixture. Combine remaining cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top of squash.
Place in baking pan.* Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate bar over low heat.
Remove and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes (maybe little less).

title: turkey brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to simmer and cook until stew is quite thick, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Season to taste.

title: squash pie
directions: Put squash in bowl and mash.
Add cream, eggs, baking powder and sugar to taste.
Add enough flour to make cake-like consistency.
Flavor with cinnamon.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pork loin or tenderloin
directions: You will need one cooking bag.

title: refrigerator cherry cookies
directions: Mix together butter and flour until mealy.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add cherries and pecans; mix well.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In a double boiler over boiling water, place margarine, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Cook until margarine is melted.
Add 1/4 cup of the milk.
Continue cooking until sugar is almost melted. Stirring constantly, add remainder of milk.
Cook until smooth and silky.
Use hot as for hot fudge sundaes or chill in refrigerator for later use.
Makes about 2 cups of sauce.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
In another bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk until smooth.
Pour into butter.
Do not mix.
In another bowl, mix berries and 1 cup sugar.
Pour in baking dish. Do not mix.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 325° until golden brown.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add salsa, green onion, garlic salt and chili powder, mixing well.
Spread a heaping tablespoonful of the cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up each tortilla tightly, jelly roll fashion, and place seam side down on a baking sheet.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Slice each roll into 4 pieces.
Top each appetizer with a small amount of guacamole and a small red chili pepper, if desired.
Serve with additional guacamole.
Yields 4 dozen roll-ups.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco mix.
Spread on tortilla.
Sprinkle salsa and black olives over flat tortilla.
Roll jelly roll style and chill at least 2 hours.
Repeat for each tortilla.
Before serving, cut into 1/2-inch pinwheels and serve.

title: lasagna americana
directions: In bowl, mix eggs, Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper; set aside.
In a separate container, mix spaghetti sauce and sausage.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Mix; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Pare and slice potatoes.
Core and slice apples.
Layer in
a buttered
casserole.
Combine
remaining ingredients in saucepan; heat
until
sugar	is
dissolved.	Pour syrup over apples and potatoes.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.
Good served with ham.

title: artichoke rice-a-roni salad
directions: Drain artichokes and preserve the liquid.
Cut artichokes into quarters.
To cooled rice mixture, add chopped green onions and artichokes.
Mix mayonnaise with liquid from artichokes.
Pour over rice and mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rolls
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Pour boiling water over margarine, then add egg and yeast to mixture.
(Make sure the water isn't too hot for yeast).
Mix well and add flour.
Let rise and then make off rolls and let rise again.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: good catsup
directions: Take tomatoes and onions; boil until soft.
Drain in a jelly bag for 3 or 4 hours.
Don't use juice in catsup; add sugar, salt, cloves, cinnamon and vinegar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry onion and ground beef.
Drain grease from beef.
Add seasonings.
Add beans and soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mash potatoes with warm milk.
Put on top of beef and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar pies
directions: Put dry ingredients in unbaked pie shell.
Pour milk in and stir with finger so you don't tear the pie shell.
Dot with butter; bake.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Spray pan with oil.
Pour pie filling in bottom of pan.
Remove crust from bread.
Slice bread into small slices and place on top of pie filling.
Beat sugar, margarine and eggs until mixed.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 325° or 350° until brown.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except French rolls.
Scoop out middle of French rolls.
Place 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture into roll. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until well heated.

title: lynne toth's punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Put in freezer overnight. Remove 3-4 hours before serving. Place in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Parboil cabbage and place in greased casserole.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and add the flour; add milk and cheese and cook until thickened and the cheese is melted.
Pour over cooked cabbage; have bread crumbs browned in the 1/4 cup of margarine and spread over all. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: nestle quik chocolate pie
directions: Cook milk, sugar, flour and Nestle Quik until mixture begins to thicken.
Add egg yolks that have been beaten, oleo and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with "Never Fail Meringue."

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend for 3 minutes at medium speed in a blender.
Put in an ungreased pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients together and spread over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar, salt, cream of tartar, soda and cinnamon.
Cream butter to soften.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix until all flour is moistened, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour batter into 10-inch fluted or straight-sided tube pan which had been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and top with Chocolate Glaze and coconut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 8.

title: jovan's spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Stir in pecans until coated.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients well.
Sprinkle over pecans and stir. Spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir. Bake 15 minutes more.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cream cheese and bacon balls
directions: Blend cheese, bacon, garlic powder and olives.
Form into bite-size
balls.
Chill.
Just before serving, roll in crushed Doritos and serve with whole Doritos.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Cut fish in 1-inch cubes.
Fry bacon in large skillet.
Add onion and brown.
Add water and potatoes and cook for 10 minutes. Add fish; cook until fish is flaky.
Add milk and seasonings.
Heat and serve.
Do not boil.
Add canned corn, if desired.
Recipe will feed 8.

title: mom's coconut pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl and add 1/4 cup milk.
Heat 1 3/4 cups milk and add to sugar and flour mixture; cook in double boiler, stirring until it thickens.
Slowly add egg and milk to mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly. Add coconut and pour into pastry shell.

title: k's congo bars
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix and fold in chocolate chips.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in butter; add seasoning, olives and tomato sauce.
Using a 2-quart casserole, add enough meat mixture to cover the bottom of the casserole.
Alternate layers starting with a tortilla, meat sauce and then cheese.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut in quarters and serve.

title: armenian cookie(not so sweet - good with tea or coffee)
directions: In large bowl, mix yogurt together with sugar, eggs and baking soda.
Add flour, baking powder and butter.
Mix well and knead to a soft dough.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Alternate toast, cheese and mushrooms in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over toast, cheese and mushrooms.
Cover and bake one hour at 350°.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chop onion, green pepper and celery. Combine remaining ingredients and mix.
Better if stands a few hours.
Will keep a couple weeks.

title: play clay
directions: Mix all together; knead until soft.
Divide into portions and knead food coloring into each.
(Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.)

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownies according to package directions for cake-like brownies.
Fold in vanilla chips.
Spread half of the batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 9 baking pan.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix self-rising flour, cinnamon and sugar together.
Dice banana and add to dry ingredients along with oil, vanilla, eggs, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Stir but do not beat; pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
This is best baked in a tube pan.
Before taking cake from pan, let cool. Serves 8.

title: spicy marinated pork tenderloins
directions: Place pork in a heavy plastic bag.
Add remaining ingredients. Seal bag and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Grill over medium coals until done or broil 6 inches from heat 8 to 10 minutes, basting with remaining marinade.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Grease 1 large or 2 small pie plates with margarine.
Pour mixture in and bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into slices to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make filling in small saucepan; butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Cook through but do not boil.
Stir constantly.
Set aside to cool.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well (will be real thick). Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done. Yield: 6 to 7 dozen.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in an ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 8 servings, 255 calories per serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Spray on chicken as you slowly smoke it.

title: chili for two
directions: In a saucepan, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat all ingredients, except walnuts, on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly, then beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry cream cheese cake
directions: Beat ingredients on slow speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: homemade mac n' cheese
directions: Melt butter, mix with flour to make a paste.
Add salt and milk.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Beat egg, add some of the milk to it and mix together before adding back (keeps the egg from cooking when it's added to the hot milk).
Cut up 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese into chunks and cook until it melts.
Pour over cooked macaroni noodles.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Roll pork chops in flour and brown in oil in skillet. Salt and pepper to taste. layer in deep casserole dish with soups and water. Cover and bake at 350 degrees until tender. The gravy is good on potatoes or bread.

title: butterscotch crunch
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler over boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Let stand twenty minutes, until firm. Makes about 36 pieces.

title: basic cupcake muffins
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine next 4 ingredients until moist.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin pans, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).

title: rolls
directions: Mix
water
and yeast together;
let stand for a while. Add eggs
and
oil
together;
beat slightly.
Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Combine flour mixture with egg mixture, water and yeast. Cut and let rise in pan for an hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Combine peaches, pineapple, oranges, bananas and cherries in a bowl; mix gently.
Fold in pie filling.
Chill, covered, until serving time.
Yields 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender.
Chop slightly.
Saute onion and
garlic
in
2 tablespoons margarine.
Add soup and cheeses and
cook
just until melted.
Mix all in a large bowl and add the 1/2 cup milk.
Pour into a medium to large casserole and bake at 350° just until it bubbles, about 25 minutes. Top with onion rings and brown slightly.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Combine pineapple and cream cheese, thinning as needed with reserved juice.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Rinse celery well and cut off bottoms, but leaving the leafy tops.
Spread cream cheese mixture into groove of celery stalks.

title: tuna fish pie
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic in oil until onions are clear. Add tuna and mix well. Pour in baking dish.
Top with crust.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix butter and Oreos and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and pour on top of cookie mixture.
Mix puddings and milk and pour on top of mixture. Refrigerate, then top with additional Cool Whip and shave a chocolate bar on top.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Dissolve gelatin in applesauce.
Add mandarin oranges.
Stir.
Add pineapple and ginger ale.
Stir. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas (which have been dipped in hot stock, just long enough to soften) in shallow 3-quart buttered casserole.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Add in order:
chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; sprinkle with oregano. Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Fill buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-lemon cream topping for angel or sponge cake
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients, mixed, in double boiler until custard coats spoon.
Add the orange rind.
When cool, add the whipped cream.
Makes enough for one large angel or chiffon cake. (Cut cake into slices; put big spoonful of sauce on each.)

title: shrimp creole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In large frying pan or electric skillet, fry bacon, garlic, celery, onion and pepper in olive oil until onion is translucent (do not brown).
Add the rest of the ingredients except the Clamato juice and the shrimp.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 hours, adding Clamato juice as necessary to thin the sauce.
Add shrimp and boil for no longer than 10 minutes.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: mom's pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in one bowl until well blended.
Add pecans.
Grease and flour two large loaf pans or four (1-pound) coffee cans.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and celery.
Simmer until tender.
Add water.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to mixture.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish (or 2 smaller ones).
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in heavy saucepan.
Add milk and butter (oleo).
Cook on medium heat, stirring often.

title: vodka collins punch
directions: Combine sweet and sour mix with vodka to taste (may vary with taste with vodka).
Serve mix in glass with ice.
Pour a little soda water on top of drink in glass, along with 1 teaspoon of cherry juice.

title: fern's bread
directions: *Can use 1/4 teaspoon each of cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice and 1 teaspoon lemon extract.

title: apricot slices(pastry)
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and rind; beat well.
Add flour, sifted with salt and soda; blend.
Spread in a shallow pan, 12 x 8-inch.
Cover batter with apricot filling.
Beat 1/4 cup sugar into egg whites gradually. Spread meringue over filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Cut into slices while warm.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Put in large glass container and let stand on counter, fermenting for 1 week to 10 days.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Give it the feed; let stand 8 to 12 hours.

title: wilted salad
directions: Cut lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Add chopped onion and chopped eggs.
Add salt and pepper; toss together.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and add sugar and vinegar to pan.
Cook for 1 minute.
Pour over lettuce just before serving and put crumbled bacon on top.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray sheet cake pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Then sprinkle coconut over nuts.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box; pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together melted margarine and softened cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Enjoy!

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix each ingredient as listed.	When
well mixed put in 9 x 13-inch
glass
dish and freeze overnight.	Cut in squares to serve.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.

title: oven fried chicken italienne
directions: Dilute	soup
with
milk. Coat chicken pieces with this mix, then roll in seasoned crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: my mom's banana bread
directions: Mash 3 bananas.
Add sugar, margarine, soda, salt and sour milk.
Mix. Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 400° in a loaf pan for 50 minutes.

title: parmesan meat bundles
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion and seasonings; mix lightly. Divide meat mixture into 3 portions.
On wax paper, shape each portion into a 6-inch patty.

title: texas sheet cake(use jelly roll pan)
directions: Combine in bowl flour, sugar and cocoa; set aside.
Combine margarine, oil and water in saucepan; boil 2 minutes.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir eggs, milk, baking soda and vanilla into batter; bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and lemon extract. Sift and add cream of tartar, soda, salt and flour.
Stir in raisins.
Mix well.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat 3 cups of water to boiling.
Mix soup base in remaining cup of water and add to boiling water, stirring with a whisk until smooth.
Reduce heat and add cheese, continuing to whisk until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: In a food processor, combine cranberries, pineapple, apples and oranges.
Blend into small chunks, adding sugar if needed. Chill and serve.
Make 8 servings.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together into bowl; beat with mixer until sugar is dissolved.
Put in salad dressing bottle.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and powdered sugar.
Pat into 8 x 16-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add mixture of eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Pour on as top layer.
Return to oven and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after removing from oven and cut into bars.

title: triple chocolate mess
directions: Spray crockpot well, mix all ingredients well and bake on low for 6-8 hours.
Do not lift lid until ready to serve.
Scoop out chocolate mess into bowls and finish with a spoonful of vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Enjoy!

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until thawed and separated.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Spread sour cream on top and chill again.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve over lettuce leaves.
Top with whip cream if you like.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Add Rice Krispies, cheese, pepper and salt. Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Press.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: happy holidays punch
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except ginger ale and garnishing items, until sugar is dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and pour into chilled punch bowl.
Make garnish to float on top with one pineapple ring, an orange slice on top of pineapple, then a lemon slice and lime slice, completing decoration with a pineapple tidbit.
Secure with a toothpick.
Serves 40.

title: company parmesan chicken tenders
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, cheese and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Coat well.
Put 1/2 melted butter in long casserole pan.
Place chicken in pan and pour rest of butter on top.
Can be refrigerated until ready to bake.
Best if sets in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven; turn once if needed.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice, vegetable and salad.

title: mother's "old timey" lemon pies
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Makes 2 large and 1 small double-crusted pies.
Best if made with thin homemade crusts. Bake at 375° to 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Brush tops heavily with butter.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in large skillet.
Combine other ingredients. Pour over chops and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Turn and baste chops.
Add green pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch water mix.

title: divinity
directions: In a saucepan, add water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and let boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Add to Marshmallow Creme 1/3 at a time, beating hard after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine the butter, brown sugar, orange zest and orange juice and melt in microwave.
Partially cook the sweet potatoes or yams in boiling water.
Drain, peel and slice in quarters.
Place in glass pan and pour liquids over.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: In blender combine milk, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Split vanilla bean.
Scrape as much of inside of bean as possible and add to mixture in blender.
Process mixture until well combined.
Store in tight jar in cool, dry place.
To use, combine 1/2 cup and 3/4 cup boiling water.
Makes 20 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well, reserving 2 tbsp. liquid.
Chop spinach if using whole leaf spinach.
Combine reserved liquid, sour cream, mayo and soup mix.
Stir in spinach and red pepper.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with vegetables, bread or crackers.

title: crunchy munchy pizza snacks
directions: Place a sheet of wax paper on a microwave-safe plate.
Cut pita bread in half to form thin circles.
Place on wax paper. Spread butter on the rough side of each circle.
Sprinkle each circle with half of the garlic powder, oregano and cheese. Sprinkle each circle with paprika.
With scissors or knife, cut each circle into 4 triangles.
Arrange triangles to form a circle around the edge of the plate.
Place in microwave oven for 1 minute on High.
Turn plate halfway around.
Microwave one High for 1 minute more.
After that, if the pita triangles are not crisp and edges curled up, microwave for 10 to 30 seconds more. Use pot holders to remove and let cool for 2 minutes.

title: date-nut fingers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Rice Krispies, in saucepan and cook 10 minutes on top of stove.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, roll into "fingers" and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: celery casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine melted margarine with crushed crackers.
Place half of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook celery in salted water for about 5 minutes and drain.
Mix celery with water chestnuts, almonds, soup and milk.
Pour into casserole dish on top of crumbs.
Cover top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: good enough for company apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter each apple.

Roll each crescent roll out and starting from the little end of roll, roll each over a quarter of apple. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, adding the rest of apple between the crescent rolls. Melt margarine in microwave on Low; add sugar and cinnamon to the margarine. Spoon mixture over rolls/apples, then pour the Sprite drink around the edges and around the apples. Bake in 350° oven until apples are tender and the rolls are golden brown.

title: saucy penne and three cheese bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add to milk, then pour in lemon juice.
Pour into graham or vanilla wafer crust.

title: sugarless pecan cake
directions: Cream butter until light.
Combine egg, sugar and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Blend egg mixture into creamed oleo.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in applesauce.
Beat well with mixes, add pecans and dates or raisins. Pour into loaf pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions. Add fruit, raisins, and nuts. Put in greased tube pan or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound breasts out flat; sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion and parsley (very few).
Place strip of butter on narrow end of chicken; roll.
Cover each breast with flour; shake off.
Dip in beaten egg (with water added), then roll in crumbled corn flakes. Chill one hour (or may be stored in refrigerator for several hours if desired).
Deep fry each piece 5 to 10 minutes just before serving time.
Serves 6.

title: coconut or egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, milk, melted butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then at 325° until done and firm in center.

title: pumpkin quiche
directions: Combine pumpkin, bacon, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in a medium bowl.
Stir in eggs and milk until blended.
Mix cheese with flour.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Place frozen or thawed shells on cookie sheet.
Divide mixture between shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook, stirring often, until onion is soft, about 6 minutes.
Add turkey, stirring and breaking up meat with wooden spoon until meat changes color.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed (in mixer), cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, and mix until blended. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla. Add blueberries and stir by hand. Grease muffin tins well with butter and grease top surface of pan as well. Pile mix high in each muffin cup. Sprinkle sugar over tops. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 or Bundt pan; bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty green beans
directions: Combine green beans and onion; set aside.
Combine sugar and vinegar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour over green beans.
Stir to coat.
Cover and chill for at least 8 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie(use iron skillet)
directions: Melt margarine in iron skillet.
Mix ingredients.
Stir and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: sugar-free strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix with strawberries, nuts, bananas, and pineapple.
Place 1/2 of mixture (about 3 cups) in a glass dish and refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Leave other half at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over first part of congealed mixture and add remaining strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until all is congealed.

title: three month muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over the All-Bran, oatmeal, Shredded Wheat and shortening in a large bowl. Cool. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and store in 1-quart containers in refrigerator. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Fill muffin pans half full.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients together; mix well.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden.
Frost with "Jiffy" white frosting mix.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: In large bowl, put persimmons, which have been pressed through a colander.
Then add milk, eggs and dry ingredients. Bake in a shallow pan about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes longer.

title: crab melts
directions: Mix cheese, butter and salts together.
Add in crab meat. Spread onto muffins; cut into quarters.
Pour onto cookie sheet. Broil for 5 to 10 minutes in oven.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat and add tomatoes and seasoning.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hershey's kisses peanut butter cookies
directions: Turn on oven to 375°.
Mix together Crisco and peanut butter; slowly add granulated and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Using hands, form into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; bake for 8 minutes.
Using a pot holder, remove cookie sheet from oven.
Place Hershey's Kiss on each cookie, pressing down until cookie cracks.
Put back in oven for 2 minutes.
Let cookies cool before removing from pan.
Enjoy.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Boil cabbage in salted water 5 to 7 minutes until just tender; drain.
Combine soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper in saucepan. Heat slowly while stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Combine with cabbage.
Place in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake 15 minutes until brown and sauce is bubbling.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix pretzels and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Spread cheese mix over pretzels and butter.
Spread Cool Whip over cheese; cool.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice and add strawberries.
Allow to set.
Pour over the top and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat mashed potatoes with sugar, milk and eggs.
Add all spices and flavoring.
Put in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.

title: brazilian chicken and rice
directions: Cook in pot on stove; brown onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add chicken; salt each piece.
Brown slightly.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Add tomato paste and salt.
Lower to medium heat; cover with tipped lid.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked white rice.
Spoon sauce over rice with chicken.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Add jello; stir well.
Add cream cheese.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Whip the Milnot that has been chilled.
Pour in jello mixture.
Whip until mixed.

title: classic cream pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Blend in vanilla, sifted flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with heavy cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: crunchy romaine toss
directions: Remove flavor packet from soup mix and reserve for another use. Break noodles into 1/2-inch pieces. Melt butter in a pan in a 350° oven; add noodles and nuts. Stir occasionally until lightly browned. Whisk together olive oil and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Add nut mixture, broccoli, lettuce and green onions, tossing to coat.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Brush on 1/2 bottle barbecue sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes longer at 350°.

title: korean barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients except the beef and then rub the mixture very gently into the beef.
Barbecue on a grill, broil, or sear (sizzle) in a hot, ungreased skillet.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until fluffy. Add oil, sugars, vanilla and salt. Dissolve the baking soda in boiling water and add to mixture.
Combine flour and oats.
Gradually add to oil mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add raisins and nuts. Drop from spoon onto nonstick cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from pan at once to cooling rack.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: chili stew
directions: Cook onion, garlic and green pepper in fat until soft.
Put to one side of skillet.
Add meat, stir until brown and crumbly; add vegetables and seasonings.
Simmer 1/2 hour, stir occasionally. Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook over low to medium heat until thickened.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste. Add mustard after the sauce is cooked and cooled.
Add celery, pickle and other diced vegetables as desired.
Pour over cooked, diced potatoes.
I sometimes add crumbled, crisp, cooked bacon. Sprinkle with celery seed.
Garnish with celery leaves.
This keeps well for picnics since there is no mayonnaise in it.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potato whole for 40-50 min. Remove skin. In a bowl, add potato and butter, mix well with mixer. Add remaining ingredients and whip. Bake at 350° for 55-60 min. or until knife comes out clean.

title: ranchero casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground meat with onion.
Add chilies, tomato sauce and cream.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Take package of 12 corn tortillas; stack and cut into thin strips.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Saute the strips, turning often.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole and place half of the strips in it.
Cover with half of the meat sauce.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese. Layer rest of strips, then meat sauce and top with another 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Add enough cold water to moisten it well.
Spoon this into the boiling broth.
Cook until thick (but not too thick).
Add paprika, chili powder, cumin seed, salt and pepper.
Cover baking dish with mush, then add meat mixture.
Cover top with mush.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: eggnog chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup eggnog.
Heat the remaining 1 1/2 cups eggnog in saucepan.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cook rice per box instructions.
Cook onions in butter in large skillet until limp, but not browned.
Combine all ingredients into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Servings: 8 to 10.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mash strawberries to a mush.
Combine with other ingredients and mix in gallon jug.
Add enough water to make a full gallon. Freeze to an icy mush, shaking jug often.

title: mexican yuletide cookies(very good christmas cookie)
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla; add flour to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats and nutmeats.
Shape dough to form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven, 325°, for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, sift confectioners sugar over cookies.

title: zucchini, raisin bread
directions: Beat sugar, butter and eggs, then add flour, buttermilk, pineapple and all other ingredients.
Put into 3 small loaf pans or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: snowball cake with frosting
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple, including the juice, and the juice from one lemon.
Let mixture congeal slightly.
Add Dream Whip that has been prepared according to directions; fold into gelatin mixture.

title: sally's beef dish
directions: Place ingredients in deep casserole in order listed.
Put aluminum foil over dish and then place cover on tightly.
Cook for 3 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove all shells from crab and set aside.
In saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon margarine over medium heat.
Mix in flour and blend. Slowly add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs or cubes.
Remove from heat and cool. Fold in mayonnaise, lemon, salt and pepper.
In another pan melt the other 2 tablespoons margarine until lightly browned.
Remove from heat. Add crabmeat, tossing lightly.

Combine crab with mixture. Spoon into individual shells or greased baking casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and then bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until it is hot, bubbly and lightly browned on top.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain peas. Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Keep in a closed container. Serve as a relish or dip.

title: raisin bread pudding for two(microwave)
directions: Place margarine in a 2-cup measure.
Microwave uncovered on High until melted, 30 to 40 seconds.
Mix in milk, egg, sugar and vanilla with fork.
Stir in bread cubes.
Spoon into two 10 ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave uncovered on Medium 50% for 8 minutes or until set.
Serve with dab of Cool Whip or cream.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: kathleen "me-maw" blackwell's applesauce bran muffins
directions: Mix well together. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Roll chicken in dinner rolls and place in 9 x 9 inch casserole dish. Mix soup, milk & cheese; heat and stir until smooth. Pour over chicken rolls; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries following directions on bag.
Drain.
Mix jello using liquid from pineapple and water. Add pineapple and nuts to jello; put in refrigerator until slightly thick.
Add cranberries and pour into square dish. Sprinkle a few nuts on top and store in refrigerator.

title: vegetables and stuffing
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
Prepare dressing according to directions.
Add soup, sour cream and onion.
Pat 1/2 of dressing into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread vegetable mixture over this and top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanutty granola bars
directions: Toast the oats in a shallow baking pan for 3 to 4 minutes. Add coconut and toast an additional 2 minutes.
Microwave butter in a large glass dish for 30 seconds on High or until melted.
Add peanut butter and honey and microwave for 60 to 90 seconds on High.
Add toasted oats, coconut, peanuts and egg in that order. Mix well.
Microwave for 6 to 8 minutes, turning the pan a quarter turn every 2 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Yield:
12 bars.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Chill 1 hour or more.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Top with a cherry.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, water and 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat until thick; add vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kinckerbocker glories(easy for kids to do)
directions: Recipe may also be made individually in glass stem ware.
Use individual stem war (glass for best effect).

title: white bread
directions: Measure warm
water
and 2 tablespoons sugar into large bowl. Sprinkle
in
yeast.
Stir
until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and spongy, about 30 minutes.
Scald milk; stir in remaining 2
tablespoons
sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir. Add and stir in lukewarm milk mixture and enough remaining flour to
form a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board
and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place
in greased
bowl,
turning to grease top. Cover; let rise
in
warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch
down. Divide
in
half.
Shape
into loaves. Place in
two
greased bread
pans.
Cover;
let rise in warm place until double.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 30 minutes. Remove from pans and cool.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees. Combine the cherries and 1 cup sugar in a medium size bowl and stir to mix.

Melt the butter or margarine in a 2 to 3 quart baking dish. Combine the remaining 1 cup sugar with the flour and milk. Beat well. Pour over the melted butter. Then pour the cherry mixture over the batter. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until top is delicately browned. As cobbler bakes the batter rises to the top. If you like a cobbler with less juice, you can drain the cherries before combining them with the sugar.

title: fish provencal(yields 2 servings)
directions: Melt butter; cook onion and garlic over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, thyme, salt, pepper, tomatoes and wine. Place fish in center of liquid to a boil.
Sprinkle with parsley; cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and break fish into small pieces with fork.
Mix soft butter and flour to a smooth paste and stir into liquid, bit by bit, cook, stirring 3 minutes longer and serve.
Enjoy!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into 2 cheese balls or one large ball. Roll in reserved pecans.

title: souper burger
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Cook onion in shortening until tender and drain.
Add to beef.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.

title: fruit cake
directions: Add oil to applesauce and egg.
Add sweetener.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cocoa, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add lemon rind, raisins, dates and nuts to dry ingredients.
Then add to applesauce mixture.
(It will be thick.) Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and sugar.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm in a 9-inch square dish.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and 2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla, then add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; add, alternating with sour cream, beating just enough after each addition to keep batter smooth. Spoon 1/3 of batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine cinnamon, nuts and remaining sugar.
Sprinkle 1/3 of sugar mixture over batter in pan.
Repeat layers two more times. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack to cool.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Clean and peel shrimp.
In skillet saute shrimp in the butter. Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on package. Add onion to the sauteed shrimp.
Add Rice-A-Roni and let simmer over a low heat for 5 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Put chopped dates in bowl and add soda and boiling water.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Bake in oblong greased pan at 350° until brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve in big bowl when cold.
Put layer of pudding cut in small pieces in dish first, then a layer of whipped cream, then bananas, then pudding until the top of the bowl is reached.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Make jello but only use 1 cup of boiling water to dissolve the gelatin.
Then add 1 cup of cold water and stir well.
Chill in refrigerator until almost set.
Use a mixer to beat until foamy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in strawberries.
Serves approximately 8.

title: caramel flan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, 1/3 cup caramel, salt and water; gradually stir in milk.
Place 1 teaspoon caramel topping in each of 6 to 8 custard cups; pour custard over topping.
Place cups in baking pan; pour hot water into pan within 1/2 inch of tops of cups.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove cups from water; chill at least 3 hours.
Run knife around edges; dip bottoms of cups into hot water and unmold onto dessert dishes.

title: orange cream cake with strawberries
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; bake and cool as directed.
Stir sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan to mix well, using wire whisk.
Whisk orange juice gradually into mixture until smooth; stir in grated orange peel.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat, whisking constantly until thick; remove from heat.
Pour mixture into small bowl.
Whisk 1 to 2 minutes longer, until slightly cooled.
Refrigerate, covered, for 45 minutes, until very cold.
Beat cold orange mixture until light and fluffy, using whisk; fold in whipped topping.
Swirl orange cream over top and sides of cake.
Arrange as many sliced strawberries as desired in cream on top of cake; scatter slices of orange peel over berries, if desired.
Serve cake accompanied by any remaining berries.

title: moms spaghettios hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Brown hot dogs and onion in a frypan. Stir in soup, cheese and water. Simmer on low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted. Add macaroni and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil.
Add oil.
Cool.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Add to first mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes or until tested with toothpick.
Frost with thin confectioners sugar frosting.

title: fresh vegetable-beef barley soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in 3 1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 9 hours (or high heat setting 4 to 5 hours) or until vegetables and barley are tender.

title: chocolate ladyfinger torte
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; set aside.
In medium saucepan melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in powdered sugar, salt, water and vanilla; cool slightly.
Slowly stir chocolate mixture into egg yolks.
In large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Place 24 ladyfinger halves around sides of ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan; place 12 ladyfinger halves in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 chocolate mixture over ladyfingers.
Carefully top with 1/2 whipped cream.
Repeat with remaining ladyfinger halves, chocolate mixture and whipped cream.
Garnish top with chocolate curls.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: mom's apple dumplings(the best)
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift again.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and stir until soft dough is formed.
Turn out on floured board and knead 30 seconds.
Roll 1/8 inch thick.
Cut in 6 squares and enclose small apple.
Place apple on square; fill cavity with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edges of dough and bring up over apple.
Place in greased pan.
Pour brown sugar, nutmeg, butter and water in pan; bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Decrease heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes more.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place bread cubes on bottom.
Layer cheese, onion, pepper and mushrooms on bread.
Combine the rest of ingredients (except bacon).
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: buttermilk pie 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Blend well.
Beat in one egg at a time.
When blended well, add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into 2 (9-inch) deep dish pie shells.
Bake 1 hour.

title: molded cottage cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in water; cool slightly.
Beat with an egg beater until light.
Add cream; beat.
add cottage cheese. Pour into round mold; allow to set until quite firm.
Dissolve lime gelatin in water and pineapple juice; cool.
Add pineapple, olives and nuts.
Pour on top of first mold.
Allow to set until firm.
Unmold on salad plate; cut like cake.
Turn onto a cookie sheet and then onto a serving dish so the green layer will be on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese; add softened cream cheese and mix well with lemon juice, worcestershire sauce, and onion.
Form into one large or two small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate
These can be frozen and served later.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine next 7 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin. Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover top with salsa.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Use chips to dip.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix eggs, butter, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper in the blender.
Pour into a greased pie plate.

title: green beans
directions: Cook bacon skins in oven until grease comes off.
Do not bake skins until they become cracklings, just until some of the grease comes off.
Pour skins and grease in pot with green beans and green beans juice (no water).
Add salt to taste.
Cook on very low heat for 1 hour longer if you like.
The longer and the lower they cook, the better they will taste.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage thoroughly.
Add 1 bottle dressing; simmer 20 minutes.
Throw out juice.
Add other bottle of dressing, peppers, onions and tomatoes and simmer for 30 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Serve on Italian bread rolls.

title: 4 banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Beat until thick.
Place in large bowl your vanilla wafers and pour pudding mix over wafers.
Slice 2 bananas in layers.
Sprinkle a few peanuts in.
Top with Cool Whip.
Slice 2 more bananas on top Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour. Mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients (batter will be very stiff).
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Cook about 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix.
Spread on crust.
Chop fine broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and green pepper and spread on filling.
Refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix
flour and shortening until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients;
mix
well.
Divide
into 1 pound butter cups and freeze until ready to use.	Makes 5 crusts.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together except 1/4 c. of catsup & bacon strips.
Shape meat mixture into a 12 x 8 or 12 x 12 pan.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup of catsup & bacon strips. Bake for 1 hour - 1 1/4 hours, or until center is no longer pink.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Form into small balls in your hands, then press out on cookie sheet with fork. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Watch closely.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in microwave until melted. Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in large mixing bowl; mix well. Shape into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters; set aside.
Combine all ingredients. Heat to boiling; stir in cut biscuits.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn over on serving plate.

title: million-dollar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and flavorings.
Beat for 1 minute at high speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cool in pan; do not invert.
Yields 20 servings.

title: sour cream cut-out cookies
directions: Cream together eggs and shortening.
Add sour cream, sugar, soda and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Mix and add baking powder, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Use Butter Cream Frosting.

title: cebric's favorite hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat. Add salt and pepper.
Place cabbage in buttered dish. Top with ground beef mixture and spoon soup over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix and pour in pie crusts. Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: whole wheat bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Remove crust from bread and slice bread into strips.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Coat bread lightly in melted margarine and then in sesame seed.
Bake until crisp, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: aunt arlene's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate and salt.
Pour in water.
Cook until thick enough to spread.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: super beefy stew
directions: Cut up meat into 1/2-inch cubes; add 1 cup broth and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil with bouillon cubes, diced celery and onion.
Add onion and garlic powder; boil 1/2 hour.
Turn down to simmer; add 1-inch chunks of carrot and potato.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Cut into dry mixture until mealy.
Add water (use more if softer dough is desired).
Mix well.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out on floured board and cut. Serves 50.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients as for pie crust.
Mix egg, milk and vanilla and add to dry mixture.
Pat mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/3 of mixture.
Pour fruit filling over the mixture in pan and crumble remaining 1/3 mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and use as needed.

title: festive punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 10 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or more at 350°.
Test with straw.
Cool in pans for 20 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix and pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Arrange carrots and onion in casserole in alternate layers. Combine the remaining ingredients and heat 3 minutes.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly. Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch glass dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put in large mixing bowl.
Add 3/4 can of pizza sauce and mix together.
Shred cheese and add 3/4 of it to biscuits and sauce combo.
Mix well together.
If you would like, add cooked sausage, mushrooms, green pepper, onions, etc., at this time.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan; spread over whole pan.
Put 1/4 can sauce on top.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add to all other ingredients in a Dutch oven pot.
Simmer two hours.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat the egg yolks and whites separately.
Mix together the salmon, sour cream, corn flakes and egg yolks, then add beaten egg whites.
Shape loaf in a greased pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut thin slices from stem end of pepper.
Remove seeds. Parboil in 1 cup boiling water with 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt, about 5 or 6 minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef in bacon drippings or shortening.
Simmer tomatoes, juice and onion until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut.
Place in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(The white part will be "runny" but is done.)

title: cherry flap delight
directions: Bake and cool cake.
Tear cake into pieces and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip with cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over cake chunks.
Spread pie filling over (cake) cream cheese mixture.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Dough will be soft.
Must refrigerate overnight or two hours.
Roll dough into balls. Cover with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350°.
Tops of cookies will split when done.

title: greek kabob
directions: In a small bowl, combine olive oil, lemon slices, garlic powder, ginger, mint leaves and red pepper sauce.
Microwave at High 30 to 60 seconds, or until heated through and lemon is tender.
Add lamb cubes to bowl; cover.
Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: montgomery county crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, powder and nutmeg.
Work in butter until crumbs.
Save 1/2 cup crumbs.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Add vanilla.
Slowly mix into big batch of crumbs until all is moist. Put in 3 greased pie pans.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer hash browns in long Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle grated onion and salt over potatoes.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes; spread evenly.

title: great whipped cream icing
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl at one time.
Beat on high speed 8 to 15 minutes until light and fluffy.

title: mom langdale's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook to a boil. Ready to use.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, salt and pineapple juice.
Bring this mixture to a boil; cook until thickened.
Pour over macaroni and chill overnight.
Next day, mix Cool Whip with pineapple and oranges.
Pour over chilled macaroni and blend together.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Mix
together and press in a large pan for crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Take powdered sugar, eggs and margarine and put in mixing bowl. Beat moderate to high like cake batter for exactly ten minutes.
Do not beat more or less than ten minutes.
Slice bananas to cover bottom of crust.
Put sugar mixture on top of bananas.
Drain pineapple and add to top of mixture.
Add Cool Whip, then cherries then nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and baste chicken during cooking.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil in saucepan.
Stir in dry jello mix until dissolved.
Chill until very thick, then stir in buttermilk and chill until thick again.
Fold in whip cream and refrigerate until firm.
Best made a day ahead.

title: spread for crackers
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on an 8-inch plate.
Put drained shrimp on top evenly.
Pour bottle of sauce on top; spread.
Use a cracker to scoop up dip.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies(diabetic)
directions: Sift flour and soda together; set aside.
Over medium heat, bring water, dated, apples and raisins to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine; stir until melted.
Pour into large bowl, cool slightly.
Stir in flour and soda mixture, oatmeal, beaten egg, vanilla and chopped nuts until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: You can substitute white chocolate or peanut butter or baking M&M's for more variety.

title: double tang lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and honey.
Stir to dissolve.
Add water; pour over ice cubes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: pineapple ham balls(60 ham balls)
directions: In a bowl combine ham, bread crumbs, eggs and pepper and mix well.
Chill.
Form into 60 balls and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3 cups of juice.
Place juice in a saucepan with sugar, vinegar and dry mustard; cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Arrange pineapple slices in the bottom of ungreased baking dishes.
Place a ham ball on each pineapple slice.
Pour sugar mixture over all.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until ham balls are thoroughly cooked.

title: dressing for cabbage slaw
directions: Mix well, adding oil last.
Can be stored for 2 weeks in a refrigerator.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Alternate layers of sliced potatoes and chopped onion in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Salt and pepper as you go.
Mix the soup and milk and pour over potatoes and onion.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 15 minutes, uncover and spread shredded cheese over top.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Peel oranges, trim off and discard white part of rind.
Put orange pulp and rind, cranberries, and apples through food chopper.
Add sugar, and mix well.
Pour into containers. Seal and freeze, or cover and refrigerate, but use relish within two weeks. Makes 4 pt.
Serve partly thawed with turkey at Thanksgiving or with chicken, or can be put with jello for salad.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in large greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: After
removing
seeds, grind peppers.	Add vinegar and sugar. Boil for 2 minutes.
Add Certo and let stand for about 10 minutes.
Add green food coloring.	Use 1/2 pint jars.
Be sure to seal them.

title: pam's sweet trash(low-fat)
directions: Combine popped corn, pretzels and cereals together in a large pan or Dutch oven that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray. Combine sugar, Butter Buds, syrup and salt in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for five minutes.
Remove from heat. Quickly stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn mixture and stir together quickly before the sauce hardens.
Mix until everything is lightly coated.
Spread on four cookie sheets that have been covered with foil and sprayed with a nonfat spray.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool until hardened.
Break apart and store in airtight container.
Yield: approximately 8 to 9 quarts, 36 (1 cup) servings, 0.28 fat g and 33.4 calories.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Boil 1 minute sugar, butter and milk.
Add chocolate chips. Beat slightly or until thick enough to spread.

title: mom's easy chocolate frosting
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Put pan in cold water and beat until frosting lightens in color.

title: noodles with snow peas and baby corn
directions: Blanch snow peas by pouring boiling water over them in a colander.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Drain the corn.

title: 3 vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, kidney beans and string beans.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Mix all together.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop or shred cabbage and set aside.
Heat butter and oil in large saucepan.
Add onions, green pepper and celery and saute 5 minutes on low heat until tender.
Add cabbage and garlic.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Stir in whipping cream.
Mix bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese and set aside.
Add remaining cheese to cabbage mixture.
Stir in salt and pepper and put cabbage mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumb and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes until crumbs are golden brown.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well.
Add zucchini, mix.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to mixture and mix.
Add vanilla and extract.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in muffin tins.

title: meat loaf sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.

title: pawley's pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugars and mayonnaise.
Add eggs and all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Dough should be slightly stiff. But if it appears dry and crumbly, add 1 teaspoon milk at a time until dough sticks together.

title: graham cracker snacks
directions: Line ungreased jelly roll pan (not a cookie sheet) with square graham crackers.
Melt oleo with brown sugar in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and spread until all are covered.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully; do not brown.
Top should bubble up well.
Cut into bars (1/2 square) while still warm and remove to cooling rack. These freeze well and seem to disappear just as they come from the freezer without thawing.

title: blt
directions: Get a skillet and turn the stove to medium.
Then put some Crisco in the pan.
Then get out the bacon, lettuce, bread and mayonnaise.
Then get 4 slices of bacon and put it in the frying pan.
Then get your two pieces of bread and put them in the toaster.
Go back to bacon and flip it over.
Stand by your pan and keep flipping until crisp.
Go back to your toast and put the mayonnaise on.
Last of all put bacon on bread, lettuce on bread and now you are done.
Enjoy.

title: dave's chili
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly (simmer) for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 16 (1-cup) servings.

title: english toffee ice cream
directions: Advance preparation:
Place toffee bars between 2 pieces of waxed paper; crush with rolling pin.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; chill well.
Whip to custardlike consistency.
Fold in crushed toffee.
Spoon cream mixture into three 3-cup refrigerator trays.
Freeze firm.
Makes 8 cups ice cream.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease and flour 11 x 13-inch pan. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: university club sauce for fresh strawberries
directions: Puree raisins and brandy in blender.
Stir in sugar, sour cream, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over fresh chilled strawberries.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Moisten the bread crumbs with the milk. Combine the beef and seasonings.
Shape into large patties and place in a baking dish.

title: christmas
directions: Put in oven and bake with love.
Check every 30 minutes. That's what makes Christmas Day.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in iron skillet.
Crumble cooked bacon.
Dice onion; saute.
Add rice.
Cover well with soy sauce, stirring mixture. Cover and let simmer 15 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed on box, using only half the water and salt. Blend soup and milk.
Stir in cheese, onion, drained macaroni and beef.
Fold in eggs.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat the 1 tablespoon oil. Add onion and garlic. Saute. Add chiles, chicken broth, tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer 45 minutes to hour.	Add chicken and cook 10 or 15 minutes. Garnish with cheese and avocado. Serve over Doritos. This doubles and freezes well.

title: valna ford's angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites with water, salt and vanilla until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Add 1 cup sifted sugar, one-fourth at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the remaining cup of sugar and the flour. Fold into egg white mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick and bake longer if necessary. Place the tube pan upside-down on cola bottle to cool.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine broth, water, carrots, and broccoli in large pot. Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 bag hash brown cubes.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Lower heat and add 8 to 12 oz. of grated Velveeta cheese.
Add 1 can evaporated milk and a little flour to thicken.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: To keep carved pumpkins from shriveling, spray them inside and out with a spray antiseptic to kill bacteria.

title: poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Pierce with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; pour over cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and fruit.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in the mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and bake cornbread as directed on box.
Let completely cool and crumble into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: fry bread
directions: Preparation time 20 minutes.
Resting time 30 minutes.
Cooking time 4 minutes per batch.
Yield:
10 to 12 pieces.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Add green onions.
Cut lengthwise.
Roll up and cut in quarters.
Easy.
Enjoy.

title: healthful date bread
directions: Combine dates and raisins in bowl, pouring boiling water over and set aside to cool.
In large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
