Stir in egg whites and vanilla into cooled date mixture.
Add date mixture and almonds to flour mixture, stirring until well blended.
Spread evenly into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool completely. Wrap and store overnight before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pastrami dip
directions: Chop pastrami and onion tops.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer Doritos, chicken, tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
In mixing bowl, combine reserved broth and soups.
Pour over layered mixture. Top with desired amount of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jello cabbage salad
directions: Melt 1 cup of finely cut up marshmallows and Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water until completely dissolved.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Place chopped cabbage and peppers in bowl.
Mix together other ingredients, chill before pouring over cabbage and pepper, mix well.
Serve.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Boil the gizzards and livers in water or stock to which have been added Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Boil about 30 minutes; remove gizzards and livers (keeping liquid); grind and set aside.
In a Dutch oven or heavy skillet, saute the onions, celery and peppers in the drippings, oil or margarine until browned.
Brown ground meat and sausage in separate skillet; pour off excess grease.
Put vegetables, gizzards, livers, meat and sausage in Dutch oven.
Saute about 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of reserved liquid and simmer about 1 hour. Add liquid if needed. Cook rice and mix with meat mixture.
Bake in a covered dish at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.
Freezes well if you wish to double the recipe.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and onions, soup, sour cream, eggs and carrots in greased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish.
In small bowl, combine stuffing and margarine; pour evenly over squash.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Drain and flake crab.
Combine all except rolls and mix well. Separate rolls into 3 layers each.
Spoon on crab mixture.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 36.

title: quick chocolate candy
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar. Layer crackers in a cookie sheet. Pour mixture over crackers, cover completely.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples, water and vinegar in crock-pot 10 to 12 hours (cored and chopped apples, not peeled), until they are mushy. Cook on low heat for 3 more hours, then mix cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Puree in strainer and return apples to crock-pot.
Add spices and sugar.
Cook 2 hours, uncovered, in crock-pot.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: joe's fish chowder
directions: Boil fish fillet in water for 5 minutes.
Then remove fish to cool.
Add to the water sliced potatoes.
Let them cook until well dissolved.
Then add onion and diced potatoes.
When onion starts getting soft, add sliced tomatoes.

title: plain cake layers
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine, add sugar and eggs.
Cream well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together, add to creamed mixture with milk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans that are greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: In medium bowl stir cream cheese and sour cream until blended. Stir in soup mix, artichokes, shrimp (or crab meat), red pepper and hot pepper sauce until well mixed.
Spoon into 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 cups.
Great on crackers.

title: peach pizza
directions: Crust: Mix flour, powdered sugar and butter. Add water and blend to consistency of biscuit dough. Spread mixture over pizza pan, dipping hand in flour as necessary. Place in preheated 400° oven for 7 minutes. (Refrigerate; let cool.)

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch chunks.
Brown beef in hot shortening. Add onion and garlic and stir until onion is tender.
Mix catsup and other seasonings.
Add to skillet and stir to mix.
Add 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup cold water; stir into meat mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over cooked noodles. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Chop onion fine.
Cook in margarine until tender.
Mix with the listed ingredients.
Put in a casserole.
Put cheese on top. Cook in 300° to 350° oven until it bubbles.
Top with onion rings and heat.

title: hamburger bake lasagna
directions: Heat hamburger. Add garlic and brown. Add sauce and seasonings. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Put layer of noodles, sliced cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix by hand, then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Chop green peppers and onions in blender. Mix all ingredients, except the nuts. Put in fridge to chill. Roll into balls or logs and roll in crushed nuts.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: rice with apples
directions: Put salt, sugar, butter and flavoring into a pan with the water and bring to boil.
Sprinkle in the washed rice, add the peeled, cored and sliced apples and simmer gently until done.
Add sugar to taste and serve with sugar and cinnamon.
Cooking time, about 45 minutes.

title: london chicken
directions: Brown breasts in butter.
Combine soups and milk and pour over chicken.
You may refrigerate this dish if you wish to prepare it ahead of time.
When ready to bake, add sherry.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and drop 1/4 teaspoon of dough (far apart).
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool and slip off with spatula.

title: jellied tomatoes (easy aspic!)
directions: Combine ingredients in fairly large cooking pan (not aluminum).
Bring to a boil, breaking larger pieces of tomato while heating.
Pour into oiled 8-cup mold (or serving bowl if desired to be spooned out).
Chill until firm for 3 to 4 hours. Unmold or cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Spread crackers in deep pan. Mix dry ingredients in melted butter. Pour over crackers and stir. Bake at 200° to 225° for 1 hour, stirring frequently. Let cool in oven.

title: tangerine sunshine cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients. With electric mixer beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, and eggs. Make a paste of the food coloring and cocoa. Add to mixture. Add salt, flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix in but do not beat, the vinegar and soda. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: peas and peanuts
directions: Cook peas; drain and cool.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cut dates in quarters.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dates and nuts to mixture.
Beat eggs and melted shortening.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan (square).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grasshopper dessert
directions: Beat all together and freeze.
Put in fancy dessert dishes or large wine glasses.
Put a little whipped cream and a cherry on top.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Mix next 10 ingredients.
Stir in chicken strips.
Thinly slice peppers and onion.
In hot oil, cook peppers and onion, stirring quickly and frequently.
Add chicken mixture; cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink and sauce has thickened.
Place a little chicken/pepper/onion mixture in the middle of a flour tortilla.
Add lettuce and salsa as desired.

title: hot cheese beef dip
directions: Combine ingredients, then spoon into baking casserole dish. Top with 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Use with vegetables and/or crackers.

title: chudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Combine sugar and cocoa.
Combine both mixtures and stir until well blended.
Spread in 11 x 16-inch pan.
Nuts, raisins or coconut may be used, if desired.
Makes a lot.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix chicken with Veg-All and soup; pour over margarine.
Pull biscuits apart and put on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven until biscuits are done.

title: 4 layer jam cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, buttermilk and butter together.
Add soda and spices.
Add flour; mix well.
Add raisins, fruit and nuts.
Put into four 9-inch round pans (greased and floured lightly).
Bake slowly at 275° until fluffy.

title: three bean bake
directions: Combine mustard, brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Fry bacon; drain on paper towel.
Saut onion in bacon grease.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon grease; add beans, sauce and brown sugar mixture, salt and pepper.
Add bacon bits and bake in 9 x 11 pan for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up.
Cook until thick and clear. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Cut off tips of strawberries.
Put strawberries upright in baked pie crust.
Pour filling over strawberries.
Cool 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip topping or plain.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix hash browns, cheese, soup, onion, salt and sour cream well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix cornflakes (slightly crushed) and margarine together.
Put on top of hash brown mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over bone-in chicken breast.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (30 minutes covered, last 30 minutes uncovered).

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon tetrazzini
directions: Melt oleo (or butter) and blend in flour and spices.
Add salmon liquid and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Stir in spaghetti, mushrooms and salmon.
Sprinkle with crumbs and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: always ready bran muffins
directions: Put 1 cup bran in a small bowl.
Add water; stir once and let stand to soften.
Cream the margarine and sugar in a mixing bowl. Beat eggs slightly.
Combine the flour, soda and salt.
Combine the softened bran, the remaining bran, eggs, flour mixture and buttermilk with the margarine and sugar and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a plastic container.
Cover tightly and store in the refrigerator for a minimum of 12 hours and a maximum of six weeks.
About 25 minutes before serving,
preheat the oven to 400°.
Spoon the batter into Teflon-lined or buttered muffin tins, filling them 2/3 full.
Bake 18 minutes and serve.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Dip tortillas into chicken stock to soften, line casserole dish with tortillas. Layer with chicken, onion and green chilies. Mix the soups, Rotel and 1/2 of the chicken stock and pour over layered chicken mixture. Top with cheese. Sprinkle with chili powder, cilantro and garlic salt. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes. Let stand for 30 minutes before serving. Serve with refried beans and tossed salad.

title: peanut butter cherries
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix well.
Add cereal and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
You can also add coconut.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Moisten bread with milk.
Then mix all the ingredients together and place in 9 by 13 inch casserole pan.
Crumble corn flakes for topping. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Great with ham or pork roast!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick of butter.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs, 1 stick of soft butter and cream cheese.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crust.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Spread can of well drained crushed pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top. Chill about two hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Blend the eggs, water and oil.
Gradually add cake mix and pudding mix.
After this blend is smooth and well mixed, add the chocolate chips.
Grease the cake pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandpa k's cereal crunch
directions: Melt drippings and butter together but don't get too hot. Combine cereals, peanuts and pretzels in large roasting pan.
Pour bacon mixture over and stir well.
Combine seasonings and sprinkle over cereals while continually stirring.
Place in oven for 1 hour at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: frozen peanut butter delight
directions: Cream 1/2 cup peanut butter and butter.
Add brown sugar, beating at medium speed until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix well (mixture will be crumbly).
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Lightly press remaining mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Cool and set aside.

title: shipwreck hot dish
directions: Grease casserole.
Add first 6 ingredients in order given, seasoning layers with salt and pepper.
Blend soup with water and pour over top layer.
Place can of red beans on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling salt water.
Drain well.
Combine soup, mayo, egg, cheese and onion; mix well.
Add broccoli and spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salad dressing and milk all together.
Mix until it is creamy.
Add cucumbers and onions; serve cold.

title: sugar cure for pork
directions: Dissolve saltpeter in small amount of warm water.
Mix all ingredients and stir in enough water to make a thick paste and rub into meat.
Drain next morning and apply the rest of mixture. Enough for 200 pounds of meat.

title: cream cheese german chocolate cake
directions: Spray sheet cake pan with Pam.
Spread pecans on bottom of pan.
Spread coconut over pecans.
Pour cake mix over coconut. Mix cream cheese, margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and enough milk to make consistency of cake mix.
Pour over other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon patties
directions: Put salmon in bowl. Take all black skin and bones out.
Add the water.
Mash up crackers with your hands.
Add the crackers and egg.
Mash up.
Make patties.
Deep fry on medium-high heat until brown on one side, then turn and brown.
You can put corn flakes and crackers.
Make sure you can roll patties so they don't fall apart.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade, condensed milk and 3/4 container of Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Use remainder of Cool Whip to top pie.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat peanut butter into softened cream cheese.
Beat confectioners powdered sugar into the mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into the mixture.
Pour the mixture into the graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: three foot hero
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, oregano, salt and pepper.
Spread on bottom half of loaf; line with lettuce.
Arrange in layers, ham, Swiss cheese, bologna, American cheese, salami, tomatoes and onion.
Cover with top half of loaf.
Cut into desired lengths for serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: graham crackers
directions: Lay out squares in pan.
Melt butter and sugar and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take up immediately to cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Using an 8 x 8-inch pan, line pan with biscuits.
Brown ground beef in skillet with green peppers; add rest of ingredients (reserve cheese). Put into pan lined with biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Grease large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with coconut; spread with batter.
Sprinkle rest of coconut and nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and place in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; brush bread with butter.
Set aside.
Brown sausage; crumble and drain.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over sausage.
Mix beaten eggs with half and half and salt. Mix well.
Pour this mixture over bread, sausage and cheese. Cover and chill overnight.
Remove dish from refrigerator and remove cover from dish approximately 15 to 20 minutes prior to baking.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend sugar gradually into eggs, add salt, vanilla and about half of the milk.
Bring just barely to boiling and remove from the heat.
Pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill freezer and freeze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and green pepper together.
Stir once in a while and mash as you stir.
Pour into a casserole.
Spread Cheddar cheese soup over top.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top of cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Melt margarine in a saucepan and pour in stuffing mix.
Combine and sprinkle on top of casserole and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add shortening, hot water and sugar.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Let stand until yeast foams.
Add 2 cups flour, salt, egg and beat. Add 2 cups flour, stir until blended.
Dough will be very soft. Let stand in warm space until double in size.
Knead 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour on floured counter.
Roll out in a rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Butter dough and sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon and roll.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rellenos casserole
directions: Layer contents of cans of whole green chilies in a greased casserole.
Top with shredded cheese.
Beat 4 eggs with 1/2 cup milk and salt.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Dust with paprika. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: eggplant pizza
directions: Wash eggplant and slice into 1/4-inch slices, leaving skin on. Dip slices into mixture of milk and egg.
Coat with seasoned bread crumbs.
Coat cookie sheet with oil; place slices of eggplant on sheet.
Place tablespoon of sauce on slice.
Option, put peppers and pepperoni on slices.
Place in 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, sprinkle with Mozzarella until cheese melts.

title: sugar-free cinn-sweet
directions: Mix together well and use anything cinnamon/sugar.

title: blueberry sauce sugar-free
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender and whip until smooth.
Pour into a small saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly as mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat; cool and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cook spareribs on bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours (35 to 40 minutes on each side).
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a large bowl, mix the sauce together (the rest of the ingredients).
Pour over the partially cooked spareribs.
Continue cooking at 350°, uncovered, for another 2 hours.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast until tender, then cut into small pieces. Combine ingredients and place in a 9 x 12-inch buttered dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's mustard chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Place skin side down in foil-lined shallow baking pan.
In a small saucepan, heat the butter, mustard, lemon juice and tarragon until the butter melts; stir until smooth.
Brush mustard sauce over chicken.
Bake at 425°, basting chicken often with sauce, for 25 minutes.
Turn chicken; brush with sauce and baste often.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water; drain, reserving liquid.
Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Blend in flour; add broth, and cook stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in 1 cup liquid drained from cauliflower (adding water if necessary to make 1 cup), cream and Worcestershire sauce. Add cauliflower.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in cheese.
Serve sprinkled with chopped chives or parsley.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans, garbanzo beans, corn and pimento.

title: aunt sophie's sweet potato souffle
directions: *Sophie boils her whole potatoes until fork-tender, then peels them while they are still hot.
If you use canned potatoes, heat them in the microwave.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Coat pecans with egg white mixture; sprinkle sugar mixture over nuts and toss, being sure to coat each nut.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well.
Pinch of small pieces and roll into balls smaller than ping-pong balls.
Bake on an ungreased sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown. These are great served warm.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs until light and fluffy.
Add 2 cups flour, baking soda and cinnamon to creamed mixture alternately with rum and mix thoroughly.
Mix rest of flour with fruit and nuts (except cherries).
Fold into dough mixture.
Form into 1 tablespoon mounds and place on cookie sheet.
Top each with a cherry half. Bake 15 minutes.

title: holiday delight
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and cream.
Boil to soft ball stage. Remove and beat at once.
Candy will thicken and change color. Add vanilla and continue beating until very thick.
Pour over fruits and nuts that have been mixed together in a large bowl. Mix well and press down with wet spoon into a pan lined with wax paper.
After cooling, cover and place in refrigerator.
Candy will become firm and lighter in color.
Cut as desired after 24 hours.
Candy stays fresh for several weeks.

title: barbecue chicken livers
directions: Brown livers in small amount of shortening.
Pour sauce over livers and simmer 10 minutes or place in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jello cottage cheese
directions: Mix cottage cheese, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Add dry gelatin, no water.
Mix.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: facelift casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Gently stir in the cubed bread, then the grated cheese and then the sausage.
Put in 8 x 12-inch buttered dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand five minutes before serving.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put in blender and blend well.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In
a
large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into loaf in	oblong	2-quart baking dish.
Cover with paper towel and heat at	High
(Full Power) for 25 minutes or until done, turning
dish occasionally.
Drain;
let
stand,
covered,
5 minutes.
(May substitute your favorite meat loaf recipe.)

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put first four ingredients in top of double boiler (over boiling water) and mix at high speed with mixer for 5 to 7 minutes.
Then remove from heat and add vanilla.
Continue to beat until smooth.

title: boiled broccoli
directions: Cut off all large leaves; peel woody outer skin of main stem. If stems are large, split into pieces for serving.
Cook, uncovered, in large amount of boiling salted water 10 to 30 minutes, or just until tender.
Drain; season with salt, pepper and melted butter.
Or serve with Cheese Sauce, Butter and Lemon Sauce, Hollandaise Sauce or Crumb Sauce.
Allow about 1/2 pound per portion.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash blueberries and set aside to drain.
Cream butter and sugar; mix in eggs and flour.
Add milk; beat dough.
Fold in blueberries carefully.
Place in well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion fruit cake
directions: Sift flour then measure. In large pan, combine and mix together raisins, flour, candied fruit (the
2 cups flour coats fruit so it won't drop to bottom of cake), green cherries, red cherries and pecans. Mix together and let stand.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients with the fruit.
Chill and serve.
This is quick to mix and really good.

title: "fat-free" congealed salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Add pudding.
Add pineapple with juice in it.
Stir in Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cakes and melt.
Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. You can freeze these.

title: dill green beans
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
A 1/2 cup serving equals 1/2 meat exchange.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When done, roll tarts in sugar.

title: gazpacho(cold vegetable soup)
directions: Mince the tomatoes, cucumber, red pepper and onion.
Crush the garlic and mix it with the salt, pepper and breadcrumbs.
Add the oil, drop by drop to form a thick paste.
Slowly stir in the vinegar and put the mixture into a soup tureen with the minced vegetables.
For a thinner soup, a little water can be added.
Add the ice and leave the soup to stand in a cold place.
Decorate with chopped parsley if desired.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Wash,
drain and cube chicken breasts.	Place in baking dish. Mix
together
soup
and sour cream; pour over chicken. Melt margarine and pour over soup mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers	and mix
with
poppy seed.
Sprinkle over dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pocatello potatoes
directions: Cool potatoes.
Dice, leaving some skin on.
Cube cheese and sprinkle on top.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss together and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Drain well.
Stir milk into soup. Blend in egg.
Add drained eggplant, onion and stuffing mix. Toss lightly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Use a teaspoon to place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° to 400° oven until slightly browned.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light.
Gradually add flour, then stir in chips.
Roll well rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes; cookies will still be pale. Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet and dust with powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: chili
directions: Mix chili powder and flour together.
Brown meat, then add onions, celery and bell pepper; cook until soft.
Add tomato paste; stir in well and cook a few minutes.
Stir in seasoning, then the water.
Cook 2 hours or more.
Add beans about 1/2 hour before done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in hot water; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in mold and place in refrigerator to set. Makes a beautiful salad and is a must for Christmas dinner.

title: oreo delight
directions: Soften ice cream.
Mix ice cream and whipped topping with Oreo crumbs and instant coffee.
Spread in pans.
Cover and freeze.

title: marg's salad chicago
directions: Layer in pan or large bowl as listed.
Cover.
Toss before serving.
Can be made the night before.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter and beat 2 minutes.
Add jam and mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown beef strips in oil.
Add chopped peppers and sliced onions separated.
Sprinkle ginger, pepper and salt.
Add soy sauce.

title: potato lasagna hot dish
directions: Fill a 9 x 13-inch cake pan 3/4 full of sliced potatoes.
Put onion and browned hamburger over the top.
Mix soups, sugar, milk and oregano together and pour over top of the potatoes.
Top with pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are done.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, until cheese melts.

title: mary bobo's boarding house meat loaf
directions: Sauce:
Simmer over low heat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; pour off fat and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt, lemon extract and beaten egg yolks.
Add rhubarb.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake at 350° until soft.
Beat whites stiff and put on top of rhubarb.
Return to oven and brown.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake white cake mix according to package directions.
Let cake cool, then punch holes in cake about every inch.
Drizzle the Eagle Brand milk, cream of coconut and then sprinkle the coconut. Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle more coconut. Cover
and chill in refrigerator.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt shortening in rectangular pan in oven. Mix potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg.
Roll in potato mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan.
Bake uncovered until done, about 1 hour.

title: cobb salad
directions: In wide frying pan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Lift out, drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Pit, peel and dice avocado.
Moisten avocado with lemon juice and set aside.

title: very good chicken sandwiches
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients; mix well.
When warmed, serve on bun.

title: quick blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon batter into large greased loaf pan.
Pour pie filling over batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
May frost with latticed confectioners frosting, if desired.

title: brandy alexander pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine dessert mix and milk and beat at high speed in electric mixer for about 1 minute.
Blend in water and brandy and beat at high speed 2 minutes more or until fluffy. Whip cream and carefully fold into prepared filling.
Pile into baked pastry shell and chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.
Don't be afraid to add chocolate shavings to filling.
Use milk chocolate.

title: apple marvel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples together.
Blend well.
Fold in apples.
Bake for 1 hour in a tube pan at 325°.

title: baked dressing
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, broth, salt and pepper.
Add Croutettes; mix lightly.
Pour into a greased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend applesauce and sugar.
Mix in eggs and bananas.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla extract. Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain Mexicorn; add onions, jalapeno peppers and mayonnaise. Cover and chill.
Add tomato before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples evenly in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: emerald salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water well, then add remaining ingredients. Let congeal.
Makes 11 small or 1 large mold.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Mix the syrup from the oranges with the orange juice, lemon juice and honey.
In a glass bowl, toss together the fruit.
Pour the dressing over the fruit and chill at least 2 hours.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: In
a
casserole, layer green beans, crumbled bacon and mushrooms.	Mix sugar, vinegar and bacon grease, and pour over casserole layers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon into ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Evenly spread the chips, coconut and pecans over crumbs.
Drizzle the condensed milk over all of this and bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into bite-size squares.

title: quik buns
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well and knead.
Let rise and then knead again.
Form buns.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Mix and pour over vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill overnight and toss to coat.

title: sauce (oreo sundae)
directions: Melt together and let boil 3 minutes (no longer).
Let cool and spread over nuts.
Spread small container of Cool Whip over chocolate sauce.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Weigh and mix together margarine, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Weigh and sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to peanut butter mixture, stirring until well blended.
Chill dough until it can be easily handled, 3 hours or more.

title: squash pickle
directions: Soak squash and onions in 1 gallon ice water for 3 hours and drain.
Bring the vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Drop in the squash and onions and boil for 3 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all together and cook over medium heat until thickened. Serve over hot buttered biscuits for breakfast.

title: leona's wilderness pie
directions: Bake pie crust and let cool. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Blend in Cool Whip. Line pie crust with sliced bananas. Spread on the cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture. Spread blueberry pie filling on top. Chill well before cutting.

title: cheesy broccoli-potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes, garlic and onion until done and then drain. Mix Cheez Whiz, salt, red pepper, garlic powder, broccoli, milk and Ritz crackers. Place potatoes in casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Pour broccoli mixture over potatoes; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dow jones green beans and sour cream
directions: In a skillet, heat the fat; brown mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients and heat well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo together in microwave.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together.
Add to cheese and oleo mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and spread on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.
This recipe makes quite a bit of fudge, so you may want to cut the recipe in half.

title: green rice
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli.
Cook rice separately; then mix all together with the butter.
Pack mixture into well greased mold in pan of boiling water.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Turn mold upside down onto plate to serve rice ring.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Put vinegar and butter in top of double boiler until butter is melted, then add other ingredients after they have been mixed together.
Cook until thick.

title: montezuma pie -- mexican
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add chopped onion, taco sauce, tomato sauce, broken up tomatoes and green chiles.
Grate cheeses and mix together.
In a greased casserole, layer meat mixture, tortillas, olives and cheeses.
Save some of the cheese for topping and mix with crushed corn chips.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Place half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add half the onion and half the flour.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put in half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over all.
If desired, sprinkle with 3 tablespoons buttered bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Before making cake batter, prepare topping.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, place butter or margarine; place pan in oven until butter melts.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° to 450°.
Put cooking oil in pan or skillet and heat.
Put sugar, Cream of Wheat, flour, salt, baking powder and soda in large bowl.
Mix well.
Make a hole in center and drop in egg; stir.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Take 2 tablespoons hot cooking oil out of pan or skillet and pour over mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pan or skillet.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: deluxe mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cube the potatoes. Place in a saucepan and cover with water. Cook until tender; drain. Mash until smooth. Stir in cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt and pepper. Spoon into a greased baking dish. Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika and cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: 4 bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all and chill.

title: appetizer mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash and drain.
Stuff mushroom caps with raw sausage.
Smooth off until even.
Place in covered casserole, right side up, and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Mix lemon juice with avocados.

Layer ingredients in 2-quart casserole, beginning with beans, then sour cream-taco seasoning, picante sauce, lemon juice-avocado mixture, tomatoes, then chopped onions, Cheddar cheese and end with ripe olives.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; roll out and cut doughnuts. Drop in hot grease until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon into 375° shortening.
Fry until golden brown. Drain.

title: karen's ham-bean soup
directions: Rinse beans, place in large Dutch oven with ham bone and water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 3 1/2 hours (until beans are tender).
Remove ham bone and meat. Cool, remove meat from bone.
Chop meat and return to beans along with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes (or until vegetables are tender), stirring occasionally.

title: kugelis
directions: Grate onion and potatoes.
Fry bacon and pour fat over potato-onion mixture.
Add hot milk.
Add beaten eggs one at a time and salt and pepper.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes in oven at 400°; then reduce oven to 375° and bake 45 minutes more.

title: melonade
directions: Remove seeds from watermelon and put pulp into blender.
Should yield about 6 cups of juice.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil, buttermilk and yeast.
Mix like biscuits; put in large bowl with lid on.
Refrigerate overnight before using roll or cut out biscuits.
Bake at 400°.
This recipe makes about 25 to 30 biscuits.
The dough will stay good in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
(Keep lid on bowl sealed.)

title: flounder creole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, lemon juice, tarragon, bay leaf, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Add flounder fillets; cover. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until fish flakes easily.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: egg and sausage quiche
directions: Put pastry into pie pan.
Flute the edges.
Do not prick. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat water and salt to boiling.
Add broccoli; cover and cook until tender.
Drain.
Put in 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk together; pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and freeze, or mix Crystal Light, water and pineapple juice until dissolved.
Freeze.
Remove 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.
Delicious! Serves about 20 people!

title: crab meat spread
directions: Add onion to cream cheese and mix well.
A few drops of milk may be added to thin the cream cheese down.
Spread this on a 10 to 12-inch platter.
Pour seafood sauce over and spread evenly. Sprinkle crab meat all over top and chill for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water to browned ground beef; let simmer 10 minutes.
In casserole dish, place layer of corn chips and meat mixture.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel (in blender, if possible). Pour over mixture in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned buttermilk donuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, then fry in pan of oil.

title: humpty dumpties
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Add melted chocolate.
Stir the 2 1/2 cups flour, soda and salt together and add alternately with sour milk to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins which have been floured with the 1/2 cup flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Will yield 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Shape into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass into a mixture of cinnamon and granulated sugar; press into shape.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: lena hall's fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Serve with fresh fruits of your choice.

title: corn-broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Combine first 8 ingredients and place in buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's chocolate date cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let set.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, cocoa and salt alternately with the date mixture.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt winifred's cracker jacks
directions: Let mixture of brown sugar, oleo and corn syrup come to rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pinch of cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popped corn; mix and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 200° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute onion in butter until colorless. Add evaporated milk, chilies and tomatoes.
Chop all cheese into chunks, about 1-inch.
Add to saucepan and heat slowly (stir continuously so it doesn't burn).
When smooth and creamy, pour into Cool Whip bowls and freeze.
Microwave as you need them. Makes about 3 1/2 Cool Whip bowls.

title: christmas sweet potatoes and apples royale
directions: Bake yams the night before serving until tender.
The next morning, peel the yams, slice into rounds and arrange on the bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Core and peel the apples, slice 5 slices widthwise and arrange in rows across the top of the sweet potatoes.
In a small bowl, combine heavy cream, salt, brown sugar and cinnamon and pour mixture over yams and apples.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle on walnuts and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Serve hot! Serves 8.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil broth and soup.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: In large bowl, mix all together powdered sugar, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and margarine.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, pat mixture on bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread on top and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into bars.

title: frosted pineapple
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling water; add cold water and chill until
slightly
thickened.
Add
drained pineapple and sliced banana.
Chill until firm.
Turn onto serving plate and cover with whipped cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk; set aside.
Separate eggs; add only yolks to mixture.
Cook on High in microwave 2 minutes; remove and stir with wire whip.
Repeat microwaving 2 minutes at a time until pudding thickens.
Add vanilla.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Mix in large bowl over ice.
Just before serving, add 1/5 bottle champagne.
Garnish with slices of lemon and lime.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well; refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: good cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, cream sugars and margarine.
Add oil and egg and mix well.
Beat in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add nuts, cereal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Watch closely.
Place on rack to cool.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Saut chicken in garlic and oil until thoroughly cooked; set aside. Tear up the romaine lettuce into bite-sized pieces. Add Parmesan cheese, croutons, dressing and chicken. Toss until thoroughly covered.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving cracker crumbs for top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1 (9-inch) crust in pie plate. Put cherries in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour over cherries.
Cut second pie crust into 1/2-inch strips.
Weave top crust into lattice work.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: french toast bread cubes for soup
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; add cheese and seasonings. Coat bread in egg mixture until well coated.
Brown bread in hot oil in skillet. Drain and cut into 1 inch cubes. Use as garnish for soup when serving.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy Dutch oven; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add broth and milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in next 6 ingredients. Pour chicken mixture into a deep 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with Flaky Pastry; cut slits in pastry to allow steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the crust is golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and poppy seed. Thoroughly stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: st. louis gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and butter by hand.
Spread in 13 x 9 pan.
Melt cream cheese in microwave until able to mix.
Add remaining eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Season with salt, garlic, black pepper to taste.
For hot chili, add 2 or 3 hot peppers.
Mix all together and pour in crock-pot.
Let come to a full boil.
Boil for about 10 or 15 minutes on high.
Then let simmer in crock-pot until ready to serve.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls. Mix soup and water in pressure cooker.
Place meat balls in cooker. Cover; set control and cook 8 minutes after control jiggles.
Cool pan and put under faucet 5 minutes before opening.

title: mom's sugar cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 10x sugar, eggs, oil and flavorings.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Chill for 2 hours. Spoon into balls and flatten with glass dipped in water and sugar. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or lightly brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form into crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Cook beef and onion until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic powder.
Heat through.
Put mixture into crust.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: avocado stuffed with shrimp salad
directions: Bring water to boil; add shrimp, and reduce heat.
Simmer 3-5 minutes.
Drain well, and rinse with cold water; chill.
Peel and devein shrimp.

title: delicious cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in water to cover until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in reserved liquid and set aside.
Melt margarine in 4-quart pan, then cook onions until they are tender (clear).
Blend in flour and Worcestershire sauce. Gradually stir in bouillon liquid, milk and cauliflower.
Add salt. Bring mixture to boil, reduce heat and stir in cheese until it melts.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Crumble and set aside.
In the drippings, saut onion and green peppers until tender.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Beat eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in hash browns, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, onion, green peppers and bacon.
Transfer into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shortcut pickled peaches
directions: Drain peaches and reserve syrup. In medium
combine remaining ingredients.
Add syrup and bring to boil.
Simmer on low 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peaches.
Cool and chill 4 hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry sundae pie
directions: Mix dry cake mix and dry jello together.
Then add rest of ingredients, 1 at a time.
Mix after each addition until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in tube pan, well-greased and floured.
(Baker's Joy works fine, but spray
all areas of pan thoroughly.)

title: beef in wine
directions: Place roast on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Pour wine over meat.
Bake 1 hour longer.
Remove from pan.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: In medium glass bowl, combine sugars, corn syrup and water. Cook at full power 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture reads 238° (soft ball stage).
Stir in pecans, butter and vanilla.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet. Chill until set.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending just until well mixed. Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good!

title: best peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend at medium speed until thoroughly mixed.
Add egg, blend again, then add remaining 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Mash with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Use shortening only, makes them moist.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Turn cake pan upside-down to cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain well the mandarin oranges and pineapple.
In medium bowl, mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and orange jello (dry from the box).
Add pecans, pineapple and oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: meat potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix ground beef, 1 1/4 cups mashed potato buds, the egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk. Spread mixture evenly in 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Prepare mashed potato buds for 4 servings.
Pile mashed potatoes on baked meat loaf as for a meringue on a pie.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer or until cheese melts. Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, butter and milk.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine and mix the sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: country style vanilla homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar; beat until thick.
Add cream, vanilla, salt and mix thoroughly.
Pour into freezer can, add milk.
Freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend until smooth.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nannie's chicken stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, boil fryer; cool enough to take off of the bone.
Skim any fat off top of chicken broth.
Add potatoes, onion and corn; simmer until potatoes become tender (about 30 minutes). Add chicken, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Before serving, take out amount needed to serve and add a few squirts of ketchup and a little milk to thicken. Refrigerate or freeze remaining portions.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into large casserole dish.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, using coarse blade.
Drain until excess juice is removed.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Pack into hot pint standard canning jars.
Adjust lids; process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening, sugar and salt. Stir in the flour.
(I reserve 1/2 cup of the flour to use while making out the rolls.)
Let the batter rise for 1 1/2 hours in warm area.
Make out in small ball shapes.
Place in pan.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425°.

title: seafood spaghetti
directions: White Sauce:
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir. Add milk slowly; add salt and pepper and sherry to taste.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust (or graham cracker crust).
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until they hold a soft peak.
Gradually add sugar; continue to whip until egg whites hold a firm peak.
Put on pie filling and seal outside of pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend together sugar and flour.
Combine egg yolks and milk. Add these two mixtures.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until becomes thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool. Cover with meringue.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: whole wheat honey bread
directions: Combine 3 cups whole wheat flour, nonfat dry milk, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Heat water, honey and oil in saucepan over low heat until warm; pour warm liquid over flour mixture.
Blend with electric mixer at low speed for 1 minute and at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining whole wheat flour; blend with mixer. Stir in about 4 cups all-purpose flour by hand.

Turn onto floured board and knead, adding flour as necessary to keep dough from being too sticky, until dough is smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes). Place dough in greased bowl, turning greased side up.
Cover; let rise 45 to 60 minutes, until dough is light and doubled in bulk.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve hot.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix well together adding enough flour to make batter stiff. Drop in hot lard enough to cover them, the same as for crullers. If they should fall apart in the lard, more flour is needed. You can substitute Crisco for the lard.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients and let stand until it beings to jell.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or longer.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter.
Add
milk, flour and cocoa. Mix together
and spread in 9-inch greased pan.
Mix together white sugar,
brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter in pan
and pour boiling water over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: fried potato salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp; put aside to drain on paper towel.
Fry potatoes in bacon grease. Stir together all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add crumbled bacon and fried potatoes.
Serve warm or refrigerate to cool.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine flour, salt, nuts, pepper and cheese in mixing bowl; add butter that has been softened.
Beat well.
Divide dough in half; shape each half into 10-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for at least 2 hours.
Slice rolls into 1/4-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Heat milk over low heat.
In bowl, put eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix together.
Add warmed milk and mix.
Put cooked rice in and mix.
Put in a dash of nutmeg.
Put in pan and sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Put pan with ingredients in another pan filled with water.
Preheat oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Put custard in and cook until done (about 1 hour).

title: chicken divan
directions: In a Pyrex pan spread broccoli as a bottom layer.
After mixing all the other ingredients, spoon on the broccoli.
Top with crushed shredded wheat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon catfish and chicken
directions: Place fish and chicken on foil.
Melt margarine and add juice, salt, garlic, pepper, celery, onions and parsley.
Pour half of mixture over chicken and fillets.
Top with lemon juice.
Put foil on top of pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or a little longer, if desired.
Garnish with fresh parsley when ready to serve.

title: squash muffins
directions: Mix squash, butter, honey and egg.
Make sure this is all mixed very well, then add remainder of ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Let set for 1 hour with foil on top.

title: pralines
directions: 1. Combine sugar, soda, and cream in a 3 1/2 qt. saucepan and mix well.
2. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until soft ball stage (234°). Remove from
heat, add butter, stir in pecans, mix until thick (2-3
minutes).
3. Drop in teaspoons full on waxed paper.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt the butter in a shallow pan.
Break up vermicelli into pieces and fry in the butter until slightly browned, stirring constantly.
Wash and drain the rice well, then add it to the vermicelli and saute them together for a few minutes, always stirring.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, and sugar together.
Add vanilla, nuts, and raisins.
Set aside.

title: unfried fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then ovals into matchsticks.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of oil.
Combine eggs and spice in bowl.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour potatoes onto prepared baking sheet and spread into single layer. Place baking sheet on bottom shelf of oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until fries are crispy, turning every 6 to 8 minutes so they brown evenly.

title: hollandaise
directions: In a blender, combine egg yolks, mandarin peel, mandarin juice, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
While blender is running, slowly pour in hot butter.
Serve at once.

title: strawberry-pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine. Press firmly into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth. Stir in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate.
Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl until completely dissolved. Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened. Stir in strawberries.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: meatballs(appetizer)
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, bread crumbs, milk, minced onions, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into meatballs.
Brown in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt together chili sauce and jelly.
Mix with meatballs.
Serve in crock-pot.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat 1 1/2-inches fat to 375°.
Sift flour and next 3 items together.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Pour into flour mixture and stir until just smooth.
Add parsley and corn; drop by tablespoons into hot fat.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, turning as they rise.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with syrup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle dough board with flour and roll out 1/4-inch thick.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite-sized pieces (takes about 2 months). Cover with brown gravy and cook over open fire about 4 months. Serves about 3,500 people.
If more guests arrive, add the 2 rabbits.
However, do this only if necessary as most people do not like hare in their stew!

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.
This recipe can easily be divided in half or fourth batches for smaller amounts.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Sprinkle on fruit.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Pour over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: easy perfection salad
directions: Place contents of jello in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Add 2 cups boiling water and stir to dissolve gelatin.
Add vinegar and 12 to 15 ice cubes.
Stir constantly until gelatin begins to thicken (about 3 minutes).
Remove any unmelted ice. Snip into partially set gelatin the tops of 6 or 7 small green onions and add pimentos.
Cut through the contents of one can of sauerkraut to gelatin.
Stir gently to distribute vegetables. Chill until set (about 4 hours or overnight).
Unmold onto crisp greens on a serving platter.
Garnish.
May serve with horseradish mayo.
Stir 1 teaspoon horseradish into 1 cup mayonnaise as dressing.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sussex county overnight pone(my mother's recipe, anna otwell elliott)
directions: Pour 4 quarts boiling water on meal and salt.
Mix well and let cool a little.
Thin with water to the consistency of cornmeal muffins.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook first four ingredients until bubbly, stirring constantly so sauce doesn't lump or stick.
Cool.
Add peanuts.
Pour over sliced bananas and mix lightly.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix milk, cheese and Bisquick to soft dough. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush margarine and garlic on top of biscuits.
Serve warm.

title: dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix all together.
Good for fresh vegetables, cherry tomatoes, cauliflower, squash, zucchini, broccoli, celery, carrots and potato chips.
It is better if mixed the night before serving. Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and oil.
Add all of the dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Combine milk and molasses. Stir and then add to the dry mixture. Mix well and then fold in the raisins.

title: hornets nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package and let cool.
Mix in dry cake mix.
Put morsels and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with any fresh vegetable.
Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half across the ribs.
Take out seeds and fiber. Dust with salt and pepper; put a generous chunk of butter in each half.
Barely cover the bottom of a baking pan with water.
Cover and bake squash on rack in pan for about 1 hour at 400° until squash is soft.
One squash will make 2 servings.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder; add milk and mix.
Spoon over melted butter.
Heat fresh or canned fruit with sugar, adjusting less sugar if fruit is canned.
Pour over dough.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Crust will rise to the top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix milk, egg and honey in a small bowl.
Melt shortening in chicken fryer or iron skillet until hot.
Dip chicken in milk mixture, then roll in flour until well coated.
Place in hot shortening until golden brown on all sides.
After turning over, reduce heat and cook slowly until tender.

title: oregon crab louis
directions: In large individual salad bowls place a layer of shredded lettuce.
Sprinkle generously with crab meat.
Then another layer of lettuce and then crab meat.
Tear lettuce leaves in good size pieces.
Place about 3 pieces around edge of bowl.
Stand tomato wedges at sides of bowl, forming a cross.
Place egg wedges between the quartered tomatoes.
Spoon on Thousand Island dressing generously.
Place about 5 or 6 ripe olives in a circle on top. Decorate with 2 or 3 pieces of claw meat in the center.
Serve with soda crackers or sesame bread wafers.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli
directions: Marinate 6 to 8 hours turning occasionally.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, butter, soup, cheese and onion. Then add thawed potatoes. Cook in sprayed 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer. You may sprinkle some cheese on top just before removing from oven.

title: cucumber party sandwiches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Allow to stand 30 minutes. Spread on rye bread.
Top each with slice of cucumber and dill sprig.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: scrabble party mix
directions: Melt butter; add salt and Worcestershire sauce and set aside. In large bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over cereal mixture and stir.
Pour into 2 baking pans and bake at 250°; stir every 15 minutes, for about 1 hour.
Remove; cool and store in sealed container or Ziploc bag or just eat it!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1 layer of margarine, then a layer of broccoli and then a layer of grated cheese.
Pour 1/2 of cream of chicken over layers.
Repeat layering.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake in large casserole dish for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs and margarine until smooth. Pour in pie shell and bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until firm in the center.
Do not overcook!

title: california snapper(serves 8)
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour some enchilada sauce into the pan and lay fillets, leaving space between (this makes it easier to remove).
Cover with remainder of sauce and top with chopped onions.

Cook for 21 minutes at 325°. Sprinkle grated cheese over fillets and bake for 3 more minutes. Place fillets on plates and pour extra sauce over, if desired. Sprinkle with diced tomatoes and decorate with the slices of avocado.

title: sweet 'n sour orange cornish
directions: Melt butter; add pepper and rosemary.
Put hens on rack in roasting pan; brush with butter mixture.
Roast at 350° for 45 minutes.
While hens are roasting, combine sweet and sour sauce, wine and orange slices.
Heat to boiling.
Roast hens 15 more minutes, basting with sauce.

title: carrots amandine
directions: Melt butter in small casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir into casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven. Yield:
4 servings.

title: barbecue chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken with 3/4 cup flour mixed with 2 teaspoons salt and brown sugar in 1/2 cup shortening.
As pieces are browned, arrange in casserole, saute onion in oleo until clear, add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken in casserole, cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until tender.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream together and dip fruit in it.

title: meringued nuts
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Add sugar a little at a time until all sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Fold pecans into meringue mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine onto cookie sheet. Spread meringue and nut mixture over melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Use spatula and turn nuts every 10 minutes. If too brown, after 20 minutes, turn oven down and cook another 10 minutes.

title: daddy's kisses
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate kisses and confectioners sugar.
Roll dough into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Insert chocolate kisses and place on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar after done.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour oven ingredients in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (50 to 55 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream surprise pie
directions: Bake pie crust 8 to 10 minutes until browned.
Cool.
Melt chocolate bits and pour into bottom of cooled crust.
Let cool. Add ice cream of any flavor.
This is particularly good with peppermint or mocha chip (my favorites!).

title: milk shakes
directions: Use the milk and put it into the blender.
Add half the ice cream.
Blend until smooth, scraping the sides with a rubber scraper when needed.

title: rice cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: heath bar ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and the rest of the ingredients.
Add Heath bars (crumbled).
Pour into ice cream freezer.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix all other ingredients except peaches.
Pour into pan with margarine.
Pour in peaches with juice on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: stuffed tomatoes a "la" provencale
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and gently squeeze out seeds and juice. Salt lightly and turn upside down to drain. Crumble bread into crumbs. Mix bread crumbs, parsley, shallots, garlic and thyme with olive oil. Place tomatoes upright on oiled baking sheet and place a portion of stuffing into cut half of tomatoes. Sprinkle each tomato with an additional 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil. Bake in a preheated 375° oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: texas pie
directions: Layer in 8-inch square cake pan in order given.
Dribble melted butter on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute
chopped	onion
and broccoli in melted margarine until tender.
Stir
in
flour
and curry powder.
Add chicken broth and simmer
until thickened.
Pour into blender or food processor and puree
until smooth.
Return to pot.
Add cream or milk just before serving.
Stir well.
Season with salt and pepper.
May add
steamed small pieces of broccoli florets if desired.

title: creamy onion dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of a food processor.
Top with cover; process until smooth.
Cover and chill until
ready to serve.
Serve with any green salad.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together each ingredient one at a time; mix well.
Pour into the pie shell.

title: grandma's chocolate pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla.
Stir well.
Cook on low heat until thick, stirring frequently.
Pour into cooked pie shells.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Debone breasts and place in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers and pour over dish.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes until golden brown. Cool and break into crumbs; set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Sift together cream of tartar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture; mix well.
Shape dough into small balls about the size of a nickel.

title: lo-cal fruit trifle
directions: Prepare according to package directions.
Refrigerate for a short time so whipped topping will harden.
Break cake into small pieces; place in a large glass bowl.
Dribble a little sherry over the pieces of cake, if desired.
Prepare the vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Add a few drops of rum extract to the pudding.
Pour slightly thickened pudding from the pan on top of the cake pieces in the bowl.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Dip fat.
Add pepper and garlic. Cook and drain green beans.
Layer meat, green beans and Tater Tots in baking dish.
Layers can be repeated.
Top with cream of mushroom soup, which should be heated for easier spreading.
Bake in 300° oven until heated through, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach stuffed peppers
directions: Drain all liquid from spinach until it is almost dry.
Moisten bread with water or juice from spinach. Mix spinach and torn bread in a bowl with the remaining ingredients.
Fill halved peppers. Put in roasting pan with a little oil sprinkled on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° to 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Baste with drippings occasionally while baking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Line buttered casserole with crushed and buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour squash mixture on top of crumbs.
Top with additional crushed cracker crumbs, buttered.
Bake at 275° about 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese if desired.

title: holiday mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water.
Press on bottom of pie crust. Beat cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, milk and peppermint extract. Beat until smooth.
Mix cheese mixture with Cool Whip. Divide Cool Whip in half.
Stir food coloring in 1/2 of the Cool Whip until evenly colored. Fill pie crust with alternate spoonfuls of white and green Cool Whip.
Smooth top of pie with spatula. Chill 3 hours.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Beat above ingredients together and fold in 1/3 Cup crushed pecans.
Pour into pastry crusts.
Top with 1 small piece of pecan. Bake at 325 for 25 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
You might need to use a sharp knife and go around the inside of the pan before you remove the pastry.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar in a bowl until fluffy.
Add the sugar gradually and beat until stiff peaks form. Add the vanilla and beat well.
Spread on pie so that meringue touches edge of crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: hummus dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Mixture should be thick enough for dipping.
If too thick, add oil; if too thin, add more beans and blend.
Serve with pita bread pieces or crackers.

title: fiesta cheese ball
directions: Mix in order given.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: pizza bread
directions: While bread is thawing, crumble and brown sausage.
Drain very well using paper towel.
Cool.
Roll out thawed bread on floured board.
Spread each loaf with 1/2 of crumbled sausage, sliced or ground pepperoni and cheese.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on cookie sheet (seam down) and let rise.
Bake according to directions on bread wrapper.
Slice.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt butter.
Add beaten egg and sugar with mixer on low speed.
Mix creamed mixture with yeast water; mix in flour.
Place in airtight container in refrigerator overnight before using to bake.
Stir dough down.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Dough does not have to rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: linda poor's lemon bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with pie filling.
Stir together well with rubber spatula.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch). Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
May frost when cool.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes three layers.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: banana cream squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, coconut and nuts in a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes. Stir occasionally. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture; pat the rest into the bottom of the pan. Place banana slices on top of the cooled crust; cover with pudding. Top with Dream Whip and sprinkle remaining coconut mix on top.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix everything in a large bowl.
Let set in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours before using.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat separately the yolks and whites of eggs.
Add sugar to yolks while beating, 1/4 cup sugar whites after they've been stiffly beaten.
Mix whites and yolks.
Stir in cream and milk. Then add whiskey and rum.
