Stir thoroughly and serve very cold with grated nutmeg on each cup.
Yields 5 pints of egg nog.

title: spaghetti with white little neck sauce(quick and easy, this is a seafood lover's delight!)
directions: Heat oil, salt and pepper.
Add celery, sprouts, water chestnuts and sugar.
Stir in chicken broth and cook about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce.
Add to vegetable mixture and stir until mixture thickens.
Add chicken. Heat through.
Serve over hot crisp noodles.

title: strawberry-banana breakfast treat
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients except ice.
Cover and on high speed with machine running, drop in ice cubes, one at a time.
Blend about 10 seconds or until thick and frothy.
To serve, pour into glasses.
Per serving about 60 calories and 0 fat.
Yields 1 serving.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Drain the Veg-All, then mix chicken, Veg-All and soup.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut the Velveeta into 1 inch squares. Scatter over the other ingredients.
Crush the Ritz crackers. Spread on top of the other ingredients.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Chop tuna until fine.
Add other ingredients.
More flour may be added as needed, or if too stiff, a little water may be added. Drop by tablespoons in medium hot grease and fry until brown.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Crush Cheez-Its crackers and mix with melted butter.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix other ingredients, then add macaroni. Top with cracker mixture and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and beef corned beef
directions: In skillet, melt butter and brown meat and onion.
Stir in flour, tomato paste, salt, chili powder and cheese.
Spread evenly in bottom of baking dish.
Prepare muffin mix and spread over top. Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes and invert.

title: low-fat tandoori chicken
directions: Heat the broiler.
(If you don't have a broiler, cook in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until no longer pink.)
Rub chicken all over with dry spice blend and arrange on rack in broiler pan. Spread 1 tablespoon of yogurt on top of each breast.

Broil about 4-inches from heat until yogurt starts to brown, 7 to 8 minutes. Turn; spread with remaining yogurt and cook until yogurt begins to brown, chicken is tender and the inside is no longer pink, 7 to 8 minutes longer.
Per serving:
172 calories and 4 g fat.

title: grandma benson's swedish toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts. Bake in a 9-inch square pan 35 minutes or until center springs back.
Cool slightly.
Reduce oven heat to 250°.
Slice into 1 1/2-inch slices and then in half.
Place on a cookie sheet; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and dry in the oven about 10 minutes. Turn off oven and let toast remain 20 minutes longer.
Broil lightly until just browned.
Cool.
Store airtight.
Good for dunking in coffee or cocoa.

title: crabbies
directions: Slice muffins in half.
Place on cookie sheet.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Spread mixture on muffin halves. Place cookie sheet in freezer for about 10 minutes.
Remove cookie sheet.
Cut muffin halves in half again.
Place cookie sheet approximately 8 inches from broiler.
Cook for 5 to 8 minutes until bubbly.

title: dad's casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and frozen vegetables; drain.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Combine spaghetti and vegetables with hamburger.
Add both soups and cup of milk; mix well.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix and chill until firm the jello, hot water, marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.
Cook on low heat until thickens the pineapple juice, sugar, beaten egg, butter or margarine and flour. Blend cream cheese with Dream Whip for icing and sprinkle pecans on top of this mixture.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water and set aside.
Heat sour cream to lukewarm.
Add sugar, onion, butter, dill weed, salt, soda and egg to sour cream.
Put in mixing bowl and stir well.
Add flour to form a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 60 minutes.
Stir down and knead a few times.

title: everyday waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Makes 3 (10-inch) waffles.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Drain the crushed pineapple well. Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Add yeast to warm milk. Let dissolve. Add beaten eggs. Save 1 tablespoon for top of bread. Add sugar and melted butter. Add flour and mix well. Knead until smooth. Let rise until double in bulk. Work down and knead again. Let rise 25 or 30 minutes. Melt 1/2 stick butter. Make dough into balls. Roll in melted butter. Place in Bundt pan and let rise 25 minutes. Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Toss potatoes with all other ingredients. Roast 20 minutes or until tender in a 13 x 9-inch pan, stirring once or twice.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 95 calories, 7 g. fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: jan hazel(dutch cookie)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolk.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt and add to sugar mixture. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dough in pan and sprinkle pecans evenly over top of crust.
Press lightly into dough.
Beat egg white very slightly and pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mountain recipe pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, water and oil in another bowl and beat.
Add to dry ingredients, beating well.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Pour in 3 small or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (a little longer if oven is full).
Wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Put a thin layer of brown sugar and ketchup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter pecan turtle cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2/3 cup butter.
Cook on medium heat until begins to boil.
Boil 1/2 to 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar, 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup butter with mixer on medium speed. Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over unbaked crust.
Pour caramel mixture over pecans and crust.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Swirl as they melt.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Use fork to blend pimento.
Mix cheese, pimento, salt and pepper in bowl. Mix mayonnaise into cheese and pimento, using enough to moisten cheese mixture.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion in margarine; set aside.
Fix macaroni and cheese following package directions.
Set aside.

title: chicken almond salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chives, lemon juice, coriander, nutmeg and red pepper.
Mix with the remaining ingredients, except almonds.

title: friendly breakfast burritos
directions: Fry bacon or ham; remove and set aside.
In grease, brown some onions and bell peppers.
Pour beaten eggs in pan; salt and pepper.
Add garlic powder, then pour over and cook until done. Mix with bacon or ham.
Put in flour tortillas.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Fold.
Heat and serve with hot sauce.

title: burrito pie
directions: Fry tortilla shells each side for 30 seconds in hot oil until blistered.
Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add chilies, taco sauce, salt and beans.

title: punch
directions: Mix and sugar to taste.

title: onion dip
directions: Peel onion and chop very fine.
Add rest of ingredients except Bugles or chips.
Blend until creamy.
Serve with Bugles or chips.
May be refrigerated for up to one week.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cherries and pineapple in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over the top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: ronnie's grannie hava's quick apple butter
directions: Mix everything together in a large, heavy pot, except candy. Cook 20 minutes.
Add candy or cinnamon oil; dissolve candy.
If using fresh apples, process mixture in food processor until smooth.
Ladle hot apple butter into pint jars.
Screw down with canning lids and rings.
Cover jars with a towel until cool.
The apple butter will seal itself and keep indefinitely.
The color is a beautiful rose pink and is delicious on hot biscuits or toast.

title: cuban enchilada crab
directions: In a deep-sided pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add crab meat and fry 5 minutes.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Add pimientos, parsley, ketchup, Tabasco sauce, wine, vinegar, salt and bay leaf.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Remove bay leaf.
Serves 6.

title: nachos
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine hamburger, chili and cheese in a crock-pot.
Cook on low until cheese is melted.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onions in bacon grease.
Add tomatoes and green chilies. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add Velveeta and Cheddar cheeses.
Add garlic salt, if desired.
Will keep in refrigerator.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup of warm water; let sit for 5 minutes.
Mix in milk and water, eggs, oleo, salt, honey and wheat germ.
Beat in flour until kneadable.
Knead at least 5 minutes. Let rise, covered, in a warm place.
After 1 1/2 hours, punch down dough.
Flatten to rectangle.
Divide in two and roll tightly. Tuck ends under; put seam on bottom.
Place in well-greased loaf pans.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 400° for 15 minutes; lower to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and set on sides.
Yields 2 loaves.
Can freeze.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables in dish.
Saute onion.
In small amount of broth add to it the soup, remaining broth and pepper. Mix well and pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine Bisquick, milk and melted butter in separate bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter over other ingredients in dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab stew
directions: Turkey should be clean and dry inside and out.
Using shaker, cover carcass inside and out with salt.
Shake on cayenne pepper in same manner.
Crisco oil should be in a large pot and heated to 325° to 350°.
Pot should be large enough for turkey to fit and oil must cover bird completely.
Be careful that pot is large enough that oil doesn't overflow.
Put bird in the pot slowly, being careful not to splash hot oil.
Fry about 4 to 5 minutes per pound. Small birds cook more quickly.
Large birds take longer.
Test for doneness at the thigh joint.
Once you eat this, your oven will get cobwebs at Thanksgiving and Christmas.
Turkey doesn't dry like most cooked turkeys do.

title: cucumber finger sandwiches
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers; put in a bowl, in layers, with onion flakes.
Let marinate overnight.
Cut thin bread in small circles and spread with mayonnaise.
Lay cucumber slices on bread and sprinkle with paprika.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, combine the sugar, butter and salt.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth. Add the eggs and mix until well blended.
Add milk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour the mixture into the pie shell and bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until the pie begins to set around the edges and the middle is still jiggly.
Let cool, then chill slightly.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar, add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture, alternating with bananas, blending well after each addition. Stir in nuts. Pour into well greased 9-1/2 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Remove from pan, cool on rack. For added flavor add blueberries.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream
sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add bran to boiling water; cool.
Add
bran
to
creamed
mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to bran mixture.
Bake
at
400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Mix will keep four
weeks
in the refrigerator, just add a little flour to thicken the portion you want to use.)

title: broccoli and crab casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend soup and flour together in bowl, then add milk, grated carrots, grated onion, crab meat with salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli and stir gently until well mixed. Place in 2-quart casserole.
In a separate bowl, combine butter (melted) with stuffing mix and sprinkle around top edge of dish. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This recipe can vary by adding other ingredients of your choice.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Beat buttermilk and eggs at a low speed, using whisk attachment, in a medium bowl. Slowly add melted butter.
Make a well in center of flour mixture. Add buttermilk mixture to well, using beater attachment, slowly blending at slow speed until all liquid ingredients are incorporated.
Then beat at high speed until smooth.

title: pizza patties
directions: Place bread on microwavable plate or cookie sheet for oven. Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add sauce, cheese and then pepperoni.
Or for microwave, put on High power for approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Set out and let cool for 30 seconds or so, then it's all ready to go.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water; chop real fine.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until it gets thick.
(Add 1 to 2 cups water or milk if you want.)

title: margaret walker's spiced tea
directions: Boil lemons or lemon juice, oranges (grated rind too), sugar and 3 cups water 5 minutes.
Using tea, whole cloves, cinnamon and grated orange peel, add 5 cups boiling water.
Boil 10 minutes and strain, then add sugar mixture, juice of oranges and lemons.
Last, add 2 cups cold water.
Mix tea when it is to be used to keep it from being cloudy.
So good!!!

title: trash snack
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar, honey and cinnamon until dissolved. Coat cereal, nuts and oats well.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Cook 1 pound sausage and drain.
Grease a casserole dish. Line with half potatoes, sausage and mushroom mixture.
Repeat. Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese and bake another 15 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt in a bowl.
Add oil and beaten eggs and mix well.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: Mix soups, water and uncooked rice together.
Put in casserole dish.
Lay chicken in mixture.
Sprinkle soup mix over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: heavenly hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add garlic, salt, sugar, pepper and Cheddar cheese soup.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Alternate beef mixture, macaroni and cream cheese mixture in layers in a greased casserole dish.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn flake pudding(mock indian pudding)
directions: Put corn flakes in a 2-quart buttered dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over flakes.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until firm, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir top flakes down after 1/2 hour.
Serve with cream, hard sauce or ice cream.
It really tastes like Indian pudding, but so easy!

title: best coconut cake i ever ate
directions: Beat and bake in three 9-inch layers for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 3 layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar, gradually creaming until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add
to above mixture. Chill overnight. Roll dough and cut. (Add flour as needed). Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: thick cabbage soup
directions: Cook meat and bone; skim.
Add onion, salt and about 1/2 cup water.
Continue cooking until meat is fairly soft, about 3/4 hour.
Add shredded cabbage, coarsely shredded.
Strain tomatoes and add to mixture.
Continue cooking until cabbage is tender. Add about 1 1/2 tablespoons vinegar and 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar. More if tarter taste is desired.
If a thick soup is preferred, less water is required.
More water is added for a thinner soup. Stir soup down during cooking.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Put in pie shell; add sour cream and beaten eggs.
Pour on top of onions.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes more.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper, mushrooms and onions.
Add tomatoes and sauce; simmer.
Make dough.
Press in deep pan.
Layer meat, then cheese, then meat, etc.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, Worcestershire and monosodium glutamate. Lightly form into small balls.
Pour tomato sauce mixed with tomato juice over meatballs.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for one hour.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 18 g, protein 22 g, fat 16 g, calories 304.
One serving = 3 meat medium fat exchange, 1/2 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange or 3 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in slow cooker overnight.
You need to have enough liquid to have plenty of gravy to serve with meat.
Serve with cornbread and mashed potatoes.

title: dulishus cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add remainder of ingredients.
This makes a very stiff mixture so I add enough water (maybe 1/2 cup to make dough pliable).
Roll dough into a ball about the size of a large walnut.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely and don't overcook.
These freeze very well and stay fresh for weeks without freezing.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: venison steaks with dried wild mushrooms
directions: Cover the dried mushrooms with warm water and let stand for 30 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons each of the butter and the oil in a large skillet until the foam subsides, then put in the steaks. Fry the steaks on each side until they reach your preference of doneness.
Remove to a warm platter.
Add remaining butter to the skillet and toss in the shallots.
Saute quickly for a
minute, stirring, then splash in the wine, letting it boil and scraping up any browned bits.
Add the beef stock, mushrooms and their soaking liquid.
Let cook over
quite high heat for a minute, tossing and stirring.
Season to taste.
Pour the sauce and mushrooms over the steaks and serve immediately.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: constance's vermicelli salad
directions: Break vermicelli in thirds; cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain well. Mix next 4 items and pour over drained vermicelli.
Marinate covered in refrigerator for 2 days.
(Stir occasionally.)
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Add tomatoes and mix lightly again.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 500° until done.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix sugar, orange rind, orange juice and cinnamon.
Heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add pecans.
Stir until all are coated, 7 to 10 minutes.
When thickened, pour onto wax paper and separate.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 3/4-inch squares.
Place in glass bowl with straight sides. Sprinkle with brandy. Dot with jam.
Cover with pudding. Repeat, making 2 layers.
Whip the cream (no sugar) and spread on top of pudding. Serve the next day. Serves 8 to 12.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pat flour, pecans and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: squash au gratin "a"
directions: Boil sliced squash in small amount of water with salt and sugar.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle more grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the two kinds of sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add melted margarine.
Add pecans.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add sauce, onions and brown sugar. Press biscuits into greased muffin pan to form 10 cups.
Fill cups with meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Separate biscuits; flatten.
Sprinkle biscuits with cheese. Place apple slices on cheese.
Sprinkle on brown sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add milk to cornstarch, stirring well. Add this to eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, salt and pepper to taste in heavy skillet. Drain.
Mix soup, water and hamburger in baking dish.
Cover.
Mix with Tater Tots and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cooked carrots
directions: Wash carrots; place them in a small quantity of boiling water. Cook them covered, until tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow a shorter cooking period for cut-up carrots.
Let them absorb the water in which they are cooked.
Add to 2 cups cooked carrots:
1 tablespoon butter, 2 tablespoons honey, 1/2 teaspoon ginger and dash of freshly ground pepper.
Simmer carrots in this mixture until well glazed and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
After cheese and sausage are room temperature, mix with Bisquick.
Make into small balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spicy beans
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet with onions; drain, then add remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 10 minutes.

title: slice and broil hamburgers
directions: Boil with jackets the approximate number of potatoes that you would usually use at a meal.
Prepare a similar quantity of your favorite egg dumplings.
Grate approximately 1 1/2 cups of your favorite cheese.
Prepare a quantity of butter for browning and while this is in process, slice the peeled potatoes rather thin; salt sparingly.
All must be kept hot, including a large bowl, except, of course, the grated cheese.
Now, spread a layer of sliced potatoes in the bowl.
Next, add a layer of dumplings. Sprinkle with some cheese.
Next, add some of the browned butter. Now, repeat this complete cycle as many times as required to fill the bowl.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; save.
Saute onion and celery in bacon fat.
Drain beans and save liquid.
Add sauce ingredients using liquid from beans for amount of water called for in mix.
Bring to boil.
Add beans and bring back to boil.
Add more of liquid if needed.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour after covering with bacon.

title: ham loaf with mustard sauce or glaze or variation
directions: Combine and mix well. Bake in small loaf pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with mustard or glaze or variation.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Prepare the white sauce.
Add salt and onion.
Turn oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Pare the potatoes.
Cut into thin slices.

title: vidalia onions on the grill
directions: Peel Vidalias and cut top and bottom so that they are flat. Score the top of the onions.
Wrap in foil, but before closing, dot with butter, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke, garlic and seasoned salt on top of each onion.
Wrap tightly.
Cook 1 hour either on the grill or in a 350° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix macaroni and cheese with hamburger meat and soup.
Add 1 can milk. Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 18 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Grease and flour pans, 4 1/4 x 8-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hilde kline's jewish apple cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over apples, which have been sliced; set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Grease tube pan and pour half of batter into pan.
Then add half of apples on top of batter.
Pour rest of batter and then rest of apples on top.
Dot with butter (optional).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours to 1 hour and 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruitanilla pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan and flour.

title: pizza:  "the works"
directions: Spread your favorite pizza sauce evenly over pizza crust. Layer on cheese to 1/2-inch from edge of crust.
Distribute salami, pepperoni and ham evenly over cheese.
Mix together mushrooms, olives and bell pepper and spread over sliced meats.
Portion evenly, in small flat crimps, the raw meats.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm and enjoy!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Remove and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Combine chicken, spaghetti, onion, celery bell pepper and 1 cup grated cheese.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; add rest of cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: mixed nut bread
directions: Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together all but pecans, then add pecans and pie shell. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour on 350°.

title: citrus rice salad
directions: Drain oranges; save juice.
Mix juice, water, raisins and spices in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Spread in shallow pan.
Freeze 10 minutes to quickly cool rice.
Toss in remaining ingredients.
Serves 8.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together with fork.
Makes 1 double crust pie.

title: hot dog bread sticks
directions: Quarter the hot dog buns lengthwise to make 32 sticks.
Melt the butter and add garlic salt and onion salt to taste.
Dip or spread onto cut sides of bread sticks and place on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and 1/2 cup margarine.
Press firmly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, mix 1 cup margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix for 15 minutes.
Place on top of graham cracker crust.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: larry's favorite cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with the flour.
Beat until real creamy.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked spinach with three cheeses
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly butter 11x7x2-inch baking dish. Mix first 7 ingredients in large bowl. Heat oil in large pot over medium-high heat. Add spinach; saut until wilted and juices evaporate, about 3 minutes. Transfer spinach to strainer; drain well. Arrange spinach over bottom of prepared dish. Sprinkle with cheese mixture. Bake until heated through, about 20 minutes. Preheat broil. Broil spinach and cheese until cheese is golden on top, watching closely, about 2 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and refrigerate.
Toast seed and nuts in oven until golden brown (10 minutes at 350° usually).
Combine with crumbled uncooked noodles.
Blend dressing (following).
Toss all ingredients just before serving so seed and noodles are crunchy.

title: spinach and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushroom caps in 1/2 of the butter.
Saute onions in remainder of butter with chopped stems.
Mix stems, onions and spinach together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and 1/2 of the cheese.
Place caps on top of cheese and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding mix in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in juice from pineapple, adding juice from oranges if necessary to make 1 cup liquid.
Set fruit aside.
Microwave, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes on High or until clear, stirring twice.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Stir in bananas.
Garnish with cherries.
If it's not convenient to add bananas at a later time, substitute drained, canned pears or peaches.
Add at time when pineapple is added.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Place in freezer.
Take out a few minutes before serving.

title: irene's potatoes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until mixed well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water and cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Mix together the slightly beaten egg yolks, lemon rind and juice.
Add to sugar-water mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter when slightly cool.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made by gradually beating 1/2 cup sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until meringue is evenly browned.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix well 2 minutes, then remove from mixer.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, then the persimmon pulp.
Alternate the flour and milk. I usually use one can of evaporated milk, diluted. It makes the pudding richer.

title: butterscotch dream drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In large bowl, combine the pie crust mix, baking soda, sugars and eggs. Beat until well mixed. Stir in the pecans, coconut, and butterscotch morsels. Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing the
cookies 2 inches apart. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned. Immediately remove the cookies from the cookie sheet and cool on rack.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skin.
Cool and peel.
Cut potatoes up in small cubes.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, chopped eggs, onion and pickles.
Fry bacon in a frying pan.
Remove bacon to cool.
Pour all but 1/2 cup bacon grease from pan.
Heat 1/2 cup bacon drippings, mustard and mayonnaise together in frying pan. Once bubbling, pour over potatoes and mix well.
Add crumbled bacon to mixture and mix.

title: angel pie
directions: With electric mixer beat cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar, extracts and whipping cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until firm (8 to 10 hours).
Garnish with strawberries.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Flavor is best if made a day ahead. Serve with any raw vegetable.
We like it as a snack.

title: tomato honey dressing
directions: "This is a tasty sweet and sour dressing."

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill unopened can of milk about 3 or 4 hours.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
In a large bowl whip jello until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
In a large bowl whip chilled milk and fold into mixture.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with crumbs and pour mixture over them. Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: quick vegetable rice soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
In large pan, add spaghetti sauce, vegetables and hamburger-onion mixture.
Add instant rice.
Simmer until rice is done.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling salt water.
Drain.
Add soup and rice.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Can prepare earlier, put in deep freeze and cook later.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 85 meatballs.

title: healthy philippine chicken
directions: In a large skillet, arrange chicken in a single layer.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover tightly and simmer gently over low heat, turning several times until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.
Remove chicken and heat 1 can of bean sprouts in sauce.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients except pie filling.
Put in the pie shell.
Top with cherry fruit pie filling.
Refrigerate for 6 hours or more.

title: sausage pie
directions: Place sausage on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch pieces; set aside in a skillet.
Saute peppers in oil for 3 minutes.
Place in a 3-quart casserole.
Add sausage and the next 8 ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash until fluffy.
Add other ingredients. Pour into a 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: wenda's bread
directions: Soak oatmeal in 2 cups boiling water.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add wheat germ, molasses, honey, egg and salt to oatmeal and water.
Mix well.
Add yeast.
(Optional:
Mix in 1 cup sunflower seeds.)
Add rye flour and wheat flour to the mix. Add enough flour to make a kneadable dough.
Knead.
Let rise until double.
Separate into 2 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper for 1 minute and set aside.

title: impossible cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch deep dish pie plate. Put all ingredients into a blender and blend until no streaks remain.
Pour batter into the prepared pie plate and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn off oven heat and allow pie to remain in oven for 1 hour before removing.
Chill.
Serve plain, with your favorite topping, or berries.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and oleo to boiling; boil for 1 minute. Take off stove and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate orange delights
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add chocolate, sour cream and orange rind; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.

title: eggplant parmegian
directions: Place eggplant in colander and sprinkle with salt. Let stand about 30 minutes to drain. Pat dry with paper towels. Place large skillet over high heat until very hot. Add oil, coating bottom evenly. Add onion, peppers, basil, garlic and rosemary. Stir-fry about 3 minutes. Add eggplant and combine to stir-fry until lightly brown (about 5 minutes). Add tomatoes and stir-fry 1 minute. Remove from heat and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Turn mixture onto heated platter and serve at once. Serves 4.

title: stale potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Form into 1 large ball or several small ones.
Roll in pecans if desired.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Will keep at least 3 weeks.

title: pasta salad primavera
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
In
a large bowl, combine tomatoes, broccoli, peas or carrots (or both), fat-free dressing and basil. Add cheese and noodles. Toss lightly and chill.
Yields 10 side dish servings.

title: velvet salad
directions: Juice from 1 can pineapple; cook in double boiler.
Add pinch of salt and mustard.
Let come to a boil.
Add yolks of 4 eggs, beaten.
Let cool.
Stir in pint whipped cream, mix with fruit. Let stand 24 hours.

title: sweet biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Will be very wet.
Pour in greased muffin tin. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: light chicken kabobs
directions: Cut each chicken breast half into three lengthwise strips. Place all ingredients in a glass bowl or large plastic bag; cover or seal.
Stir or turn to coat.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: punch base recipe
directions: Boil water and sugar until thick.
Let cool.
Add juices. Combine some of the juice mixture with the bananas and blend until smooth.
Mix all together and freeze in Baggies.

title: cinnamon pudding mix
directions: Sift together last four ingredients.
Combine together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Spread into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour brown sugar over batter.
Sprinkle with nuts (chopped).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: one dish meal(zucchini squash casserole)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet or cook in microwave oven. Drain.
Saute zucchini, onions and garlic in margarine (and oil if used).
Add cooked rice, tomatoes, salt, pepper, thyme and oregano.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat pineapple and all but 3/4 cup of juice.
Use juice and cornstarch to thicken; pour into crust. Bake until brown.

title: triple chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugars until fluffy, using electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until well combined.
Fold in chips and pecans. Spray sheets with cooking spray or grease sheets.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will be light in color, even at end of baking time.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli
and drain.
Chop.
Add other ingredients and mix with broccoli.	In
casserole dish, bake 30 minutes at 350°. Put buttered
bread, cracker crumbs or grated cheese on top.

title: baked apples(microwave; fruit)
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Cut each quarter into 3 wedges. Arrange in a baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and spices over apples.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a microwave for 15 minutes on High, stirring once!

title: brownies
directions: Melt together butter and cocoa; set aside.
Blend sugar and eggs.
Put in chocolate mixture, then add the rest of the ingredients and blend together.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: betty's bread
directions: Mix water and yeast with whip.
Add sugar, salt and
2 cups flour.
Whip until mixed.
Add egg, vegetable oil and about 3 cups flour.
Stir with spoon until sticky.
Knead in rest of flour. Can use same bowl.
Wash bowl and oil.
Put mixture into bowl and roll around in oil.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Let rise twice, then shape into rolls or loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° the loaves 1 hour.
Rolls less.

title: food for angels
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, gradually add sugar and vanilla, fold in crackers and nuts.
Place in buttered pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Can be frozen.
Can decorate with cherries.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, oil, egg, vanilla, salt, dry milk and sugar substitute until fluffy.
In separate bowl, mix flour and soda.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture. Chop chocolate bar and stir into batter.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet that has been lightly sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake for 12 minutes or until brown. Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: jewish chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs well.
Mix brown sugar with egg.
Place on stove in pan of water and cook 15 minutes.
Stir while it's cooking to keep from turning into sugar.
Let cool.
Add baking powder, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 1/2 hour.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Add dates, if desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; let cool, then place in a jar and refrigerate.
Combine spinach, eggs, mushrooms, bacon and purple onion; toss.
Shake dressing vigorously before pouring over salad. Add croutons, if you like.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt well.
Add flour (about 1 cup) to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured surface very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll loosely like cinnamon roll and cut.
Put into boiling broth and cook unti just barely tender.
Cover and let set a few minutes.

title: five layer dip
directions: First Layer:
Combine refried beans, bean dip, 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt, chili powder and minced onion.
Mix well.

title: overnight chicken salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on bottom and sides of bowl.
Layer chestnuts, chicken, cheese, bacon and onions.
Mix together salad dressing and buttermilk dressing.
Spread on top of salad mixture, sealing edges of bowl.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and bacon if you desire.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine corn, pepper, pimento, celery, cucumber and onion. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently and chill 8 to 10 hours.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into rolls and wrap in plastic wrap.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Remove plastic wrap; place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Prepare artichokes by cutting off stems even with base.
Peel stems and set aside.
Snap off the small lower leaves and discard. Snip off thorns.
Take each artichoke and bang on edge of a counter to open leaves.

title: praline holiday pie
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and nuts into saucepan; heat until butter and sugar melt.
Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until bubbly; cool.

title: brunswick stew
directions: *An equal amount of fresh cooked chicken will do.

title: white punch
directions: Pour soda into ice ring.
Freeze until firm.
Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add grape juice and citric acids.
Mix well.
Chill until serving time. Unmold ice ring into punch bowl.
Pour punch mixture over top. Spoon in sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potato until tender; slice while hot.
Broil bacon until crisp; pour off fat and add water.
Thicken with flour and sugar mixed together.
Add onions, vinegar and seasonings; bring to a boil and mix with hot potatoes.

title: lettuce california salad
directions: Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: mac & cheese
directions: Stir together ingredients and put in a crockpot.
Top with cheese and cook for 3 hours on low.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into a ball.
When ready to serve, pour 1/2 cup of cocktail sauce over crab ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick italian cream cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, buttermilk, egg whites, egg and oil, beating until well blended. In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, coconut and pecans together. Add to first bowl. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: bob's old-fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries, just until moistened. Gently stir berries into mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Add to crust.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: miriam's frosting
directions: Use Pillsbury Plus yellow cake mix.
Mix ingredients together. Place in fridge to cool.
Frost on cool cake only.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix other dry ingredients.
Mix raisins, apples, nuts and preserves.
Add to sugar alternately with flour mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Place in mixing bowl, chocolate chips, chocolate bar, Marshmallow Creme, butter and nuts.
Bring evaporated milk and sugar to a boil on medium heat; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over ingredients in bowl.
Stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: west indies rice and peas
directions: Boil peas, seasoning, coconut milk and bacon in a pot of the 6 cups of water.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as box directs; let cool.
Break cake into chunks.
Put in the bottom of punch bowl.
Pour pineapple, including juice, over cake.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Microwave soup, milk, noodles, peas, pimento and tuna on High 9 minutes, stirring 2 times.
In small pan, heat butter; add crumbs.
Sprinkle noodles with crumb mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients, one at a time.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Grease bottom only of metal 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pumpkin mix in.
Spread dry cake mix over pumpkin evenly, then sprinkle with pecans.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (check at 50 minutes).

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix remaining ingredients carefully (except sour cream).
Let set and top with sour cream.

title: sunday morning coffee cake
directions: Combine milk, egg, sugar and shortening.
Sift 1 cup flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, 1 tablespoon flour, butter and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer the following:
sliced potatoes, salt and pepper to taste, sliced carrots, peas, rice, ground beef and onion.
Mix the soup and water together, and pour over.
Bake without cover about 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together and press into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together Bisquick, cornmeal and baking powder.
In a small bowl, beat together the remaining ingredients. Pour liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix just until moistened.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square baking pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with honey butter.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple and save liquid.
Add water to liquid to measure to 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup reserved juice with water. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip with whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6-cup mold and refrigerate until firm. Unmold and serve.

title: spicy cranberry soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large kettle, place cranberries, water and both sugars.
Heat to boiling and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes or until the berry skins pop.
Drain, reserving 3 1/2 cups of the liquid.
Place berries in blender or food processor and puree, then strain to remove skins.
Mix with reserved liquid and place in large saucepan.
Add wine, hot pepper sauce, spices and lemon peel.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix the flour, salt and sugar together.
Beat eggs with milk; add dry ingredients.
Pour on hot griddle; bake until bubbles form.
Turn over and brown the other side.

title: carrot-oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, cream margarine, sugar and Sweet 'N Low.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, carrots and pecans.

title: mom's low-fat fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and spices in plastic bag or in bowl.
Coat chicken in seasoned flour.
Heat tablespoon oil in large nonstick skillet.
Quickly add chicken.
Brown over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes per side, until golden brown on all sides.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from skillet and place on a cookie sheet which has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake until done (approximately 30 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the egg mixture.
Add the squash, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans or a large Bundt pan at 325° for
1 hour.

title: chicken scandia(yields 4 servings)
directions: Grill or saute chicken.
In a small saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients; heat over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. For each serving, slice chicken diagonally across grain into 4 slices.
Arrange on a bed of noodles and spoon gravy mixture over. Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: company bread pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine egg yolks, cottage cheese, milk, 1/2 cup of the sugar, the butter or margarine, allspice, mace, cloves and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in bread cubes and raisins. Turn into 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Spoon cranberry sauce atop.
Beat egg whites until peaks form (tips curl over). Gradually add the remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Spread over cranberry sauce. Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs with water.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll out thin.
Place in sun to dry.
Roll again.
Slice fine.
Put in boiling water or broth.
Cook 15 minutes, covered at reduced heat.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Pour oil and milk all at once into flour mixture.
Mix together lightly (add a little more flour if too moist).
Add grated cheese.
Roll out, cut and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes approximately 20 to 24 biscuits.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Mix dirt, swamp water, crushed bones and fat.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Add grass, muddy water, and squash bugs.
Stir until bugs dissolve.
Drop on waxed paper; let cool.

title: granny hogue's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Cook in oven 1 hour at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar,
flour
and	spices.
Add
oil and mix well. Add 1 egg
at
a	time and mix.
Add carrots and mix, then add raisins and
walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Reserve 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese for topping.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons oleo and stir in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Stir in cheese and sour cream until melted. Combine ham and cauliflower with cheese sauce.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: 15-minute stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and reserve.
Cut meat diagonally across grain in very thin strips.
Heat fat in skillet until you have about 3 tablespoons melted fat (if necessary, add butter); remove trimmings.
Brown meat.
Add 2/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix.
Heat to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens; sauce will be thin.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Soak peelings in salt water overnight.
Cut peelings in strips.
Boil and pour off water 3 times.
Mix sugar, 1/2 cup of water and peelings.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook slowly until peel is translucent.
Drain.
Roll in sugar and dry on rack. Store in airtight can.

title: 2 chess pies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, beaten with 2 tablespoons water.
Add other 2 tablespoons water.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cup
directions: Measure 4 cups of the juice drained from the mandarin oranges and peaches into a saucepan and add strawberry Jell-O, vanilla pudding mix and tapioca; cook together.
Then add frozen strawberries.
When cool, add oranges and peaches.
You may use pineapple, if desired.
Add bananas before serving.
Keeps good.

title: chicken casserole 2
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove all skin and bones.
Chop into fairly large pieces. Simmer soups and chicken broth until hot. Toss stuffing mix and melted butter until well coated.
Put about 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of baking dish sprayed with Pam. Add chicken pieces and then add soup mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown
hamburger and onion and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with sour cream. Top with Mozzarella. Unroll crescent rolls and spread on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top. Bake 20 minutes.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy in whipping cream.
Add other ingredients.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, bananas and nuts.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry cream dessert
directions: Break up angel food cake and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan (press down to form a makeshift crust).
Cut up strawberries (all but 10 to 15) in small pieces and layer over cake.

title: yummy fudge cookies
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stir margarine and chocolate until melted and smooth.
Cool.
Stir in 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla and nuts until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt) until well blended.
Cover and chill 1 1/2 to 2 hours until firm.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll balls in remaining 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven 20 minutes or until crackled on top and slightly firm to touch.
Immediately remove to rack to cool.
Store tightly covered in cool place up to 1 week.
Can be frozen.

title: chili con carne
directions: Chop up Italian sausage with fork in frying pan.
Saute until it turns brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Drain mixture on paper towels.
Pat with towels on top to absorb grease.
Put mixture in soup pan; add rest of ingredients, including spices.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding water as needed.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage as for slaw.
Boil 20 minutes in salt water; drain.
Place layer of cabbage in buttered baking dish.
Dot cabbage with butter and sprinkle with pepper.
Cover with layer of cracker crumbs.
Repeat layer to fill dish, ending with a layer of crackers.
Cover with milk.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: apple cheese
directions: Lightly chop apples and drain.
Stir together sugar, margarine and flour.
This mix will be crumbly.
Fold in Velveeta cheese. Place drained apples in bottom of 6 x 9-inch dish.
Pat cheese mixture on top of apples to cover.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 minutes uncovered, then tent with foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
While still warm, slice in a bowl. Mix all other ingredients with rotary mixer.
Pour over potatoes and let stand for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Finely chop onions and water chestnuts and mix all ingredients (use dry soup mix).
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: meal in a pumpkin
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown hamburger meat, onion and soy sauce.
Mix everything together, then cut pumpkin top out and clean out; put mixture together in pumpkin.
Draw a face with a permanent marker on the pumpkin and put it in the oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: perfect orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O mix (dry), oil, orange juice, water and orange peel in a large bowl and beat well with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes, until cake tests done.
Invert cake onto serving platter.
Ice with Orange Glaze while warm.

title: cherry cake
directions: You will need a ring pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy.
In another bowl, mix pudding with milk; stir until thick.
Combine cream cheese with pudding.
Using a wire whisk, mix in Cool Whip and vanilla; set aside.
Crush Oreos until very fine.
Layer in flowerpot starting with Oreos, cream cheese mixture and Oreos (end with layer of Oreos).
Add flower, gummy worms and serve with shovel.
Have fun!

title: reese's pieces chocolate cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Let cool on cookie sheets slightly before removing.

title: cape cod cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and orange juice.
Sift flour and soda together and add to liquid.
Blend well.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, oats, egg, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle butter evenly over crumb mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, until apples are tender.

title: sugar cookies(over 150 year old recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream sugars, shortening and vanilla. Add eggs; beat until fluffy. Add baking soda to buttermilk and beat until it bubbles. Mix dry ingredients. Alternate adding milk and flour to batter. Drop a heaping teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove cookies and sprinkle with white sugar. Makes 4 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in order given.
Blend just until mixed.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes its own crust.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients in order given and mix well by hand.
Grease muffin tins or spray with Pam and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix Bisquick and water to make a soft dough.
Beat vigorously with fork for 20 strokes.
Smooth into ball.
Knead on floured board 5 times.
Roll out and put into 9-inch Pyrex dish.

title: pit type barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Perfect accompaniment to pre-seasoned oven roast.

title: rancho beans
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Add hamburger and bacon; brown.
Mix in the remaining ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 30 minute yeast bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; let rest for 15 minutes.
Add eggs and salt; mix well.
After this is mixed, add the flour, until manageable, then you make into rolls.
After you make into rolls, let them set for 10 minutes, then put into oven at 350° to 375° and bake until brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen rolls.

title: oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Beat in eggs.
Combine oats, flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture. Add vanilla and crushed pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions for 2 layers. Cool.

title: ruby's pecan brown sugar bars
directions: Mix margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool well before cutting into bars.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter, blend in flour; gradually add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Mix until smooth, cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in browned meat.
Pour into casserole dish, bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover with corn chips, cheese and lettuce before serving.

title: five can baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 of sausage and mix well. Pour into large baking dish.
Place rest of sausage on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: olive mexican fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a large deep skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili seasoning.
Simmer (uncovered) for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans, corn and olives.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
In a 2-quart casserole layer chips, then meat mixture, making several layers.
Sprinkle cheese on top and arrange chips around the edge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables with creamy Italian dressing and marinate overnight or at least 3 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook 1 hour, uncovered.
Put into jars and pressure 5 minutes at 10 pounds.

title: microwave sugarless apple pie
directions: Microwave apple juice on High 1 minute or until thawed.
Stir in cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in apples and margarine. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir. Microwave on High 5 minutes or until apples are fork-tender. Cool 20 to 30 minutes.
Spoon into crust.

title: orange glazed beets
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in orange juice.
Cook over medium heat and stir until thick. Add butter and beets and heat thoroughly.

title: one skillet supper
directions: Fry potatoes in a large skillet with Crisco.
Salt and pepper while frying.
When potatoes are nearly done, add smoked sausage. Heat on low, stirring often until sausage is warm.
Pour eggs over potato mixture and stir often; eggs will cook around potatoes and sausage.
When done, but not too brown, sprinkle with cheese. Simmer a couple of minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cook pinto beans with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender and mash.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then turn down to 300° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix vinegar and prepared mustard.
Add water, sugar, salt and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over hard-boiled eggs and onion slices.
Refrigerate.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, oats, soup mix and catsup.
Shape into a loaf pan.
Put a few bacon strips over top or baste with catsup.
Bake until done at 375° for 1 hour.

title: marinara spaghetti
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: beefed up biscuit casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Drain the fat off. Stir in the tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Separate the 10 biscuits.
Put 5 biscuits in a well-greased casserole dish and cook in oven until almost brown. Take out of oven.
In a bowl, put 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese (save remaining cheese to put over top), sour cream and egg and mix together well.
Pour into the meat mixture.
Spoon all of these mixtures together and pour over the 5 biscuits.
Put the remaining 5 cooked biscuits over this.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening with a fork.
Add water, one tablespoon at a time.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft at 375°; let cool.
Peel top of potatoes; scoop out the insides and place in one bowl.
Mix Italian dressing, milk and spices to a mashed potato consistency. Place mashed potatoes back in shells of baked potatoes.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Place in oven at 375° or until cheese melts, then serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple; place in deep bowl.
Add jello and mix.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows; mix well.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: shell macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix with shredded or grated cheese. Add mayonnaise, onions, relish and Spam. Add extra mayonnaise, if desired. Chill and serve.

title: ground beef and macaroni
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in onion.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Microwave on 30% power for 25 to 30 minutes or until macaroni is just tender, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving. Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Put together and press in pie pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls or cups
directions: Mix together; roll into a ball and dip in melted chocolate. If placing in cups, pour some chocolate over the ball when in the cup.

title: italian delight
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Melt butter.
Add chopped onions and cook until nearly brown.
Add ground beef and cook until ground beef is nearly done.
Add corn, olives, tomato juice, cheese, salt, pepper, green pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Bake one hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: speedy salmon fillet
directions: Rinse salmon; pat dry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture in a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: can soup
directions: Mix all together. Very good soup on a cold winter day.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: You must do this first!
Oven has to be hot!
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: greek quesadillas
directions: Saute onion in hot oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 6 minutes or until tender. Add garlic and saut 1 minute; add spinach and saut 3 to 4 minutes or until spinach is slightly wilted. Drain mixture on paper towels; cool slightly. Wipe skillet clean and set aside. Stir together Feta cheese and next 7 ingredients until blended. Gently stir in spinach mixture. Spoon mixture evenly onto half of each tortilla. Fold in half, pressing gently to seal.

title: special roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Add all ingredients to roast, except for tomato paste and wine.
Dilute tomato paste with wine and then pour over roast.
Place roast in oven and cook uncovered for 1 hour at 400°.
Cook roast covered for an additional 1 1/2 hours at same temperature or until tender.
Add water as needed, if roast gets dry.

title: chow mein noodles
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch; mix together and drop on wax paper.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients, vinegar and flavoring; mix well.
Drop teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Sprinkle a little granulated sugar on each cookie.
Bake in a moderately hot oven, 400°, for about 12 minutes, or until delicately browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to dissolve, then cool.
Add all ingredients and serve.

title: leftover chicken
directions: Mix chicken, macaroni, cheese and cream of chicken soup with a little milk.
Brown bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add about 1/2 cup milk to casserole and add bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: appetizer meatballs in spicy sauce
directions: In a pan combine sugar, sauce, lemon juice, garlic salt and wine.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and allow to simmer 20 minutes.
Cook onion, carrot and potato; combine with meat, salt and egg.
Shape into large marble size balls.
Arrange in shallow pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until browned and cooked through.
Remove and add to prepared sauce; then stir in juices from meat.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the crumbs in a mixing bowl.
Add the sugar and butter, mixing well.
Place crumb mixture in a 10-inch spring-form pan, pressing up one inch on the sides of pan. Run a knife around the edge of the sides to even.
Press crumbs into bottom of pan evenly.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and allow to cool before filling.

title: brown bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add onion, cucumber, tomatoes, celery, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add Miracle Whip; chill and serve.

title: mock pizzas
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread over bread of choice (English muffins work well).
Bake until bubbly.
Stores for 3 weeks.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: Beat sugar and egg whites until stiff.
Reserve 2 tablespoons. Fold vanilla into remaining whites.
Add almond extract, cinnamon and nuts.
Knead so that mixture does not stick.
Roll 1 cm. thick. Cut with star cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with ground hazelnuts or confectioners sugar.
Arrange on greased baking sheet.
Brush with reserved egg white (if necessary, add a few drops of water).
Bake at 150° C for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bacon-tomato cups
directions: Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion.
Grate cheese (3/4 cup).
Mix all ingredients, except biscuits; set aside.
Separate each biscuit into 3 thinner biscuits; lay each biscuit over a mini muffin pan cup.
Press with floured fingers into hole or cup. Fill each cup with bacon mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in recipe order, topping with Parmesan cheese.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise with sugar and pour on top of layered salad.
Do not mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, mix together.

title: apricot pie
directions: Bake crust in a 10-inch pie plate.
Place water and apricots in saucepan and bring to a boil, simmer 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth; whip cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pie crust and place in refrigerator until apricot topping is ready.
Put jello in large bowl.
Measure 2 cups hot juice from cooked apricots.
Add juice to jello and stir until it is dissolved.
Whip apricots with 6 tablespoons sugar and add to gelatin mixture.
Add salt; let cool and thicken.
Pour over cheese mixture.

title: coconut pies
directions: Butter unbaked pie shells (2); spread coconut onto crust.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla together and pour into shells. Bake at 375° until middle is firm.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour and salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Add pecans; shape into a 1-inch ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Pinch angel food cake into bite size pieces. Mix pudding by package directions. Layer cake pieces, pudding and crushed Butterfingers. There should be enough for 2 layers of each if a large oblong container is used. A punch bowl will have several layers. Top with Cool Whip and crushed Butterfingers. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except for Cheddar cheese).
Put in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Then add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight to chill.

title: sour cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to cheese and sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture. Grease cups of miniature muffin pans with margarine.
Place graham cracker crumbs in pan and dump out.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then top with mixture of sour cream, sugar and vanilla.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook together until sausage is done.
To this add 1 cup of rice and 1 cup of slivered almonds.
Cook this mixture in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if it gets dry.

title: north pole punch
directions: In punch bowl or pitcher, combine Hi-C Hula Punch and ice cream.
Stir until well blended.
Chill. Just before serving, add Sprite. Serve in punch cups or tall soda glasses.
Serves 32.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Prepare each Jell-O and mix with 1 1/4 cup hot water and 1 teaspoon of plain gelatin for each package of Jell-O.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, boil pineapple juice and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon of gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and add to juice.
Cool.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon and onion over crust.
Add ham and cheese. Beat eggs, mustard and cream.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top; bake at 350°.
Green pepper and mushrooms may also be added to the sauteed onions.

title: pineapple tarts
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and milk alternately with graham crackers and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into baking cups and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Measure all dry ingredients (except sugar) into one bowl. Take sugar and shortening and cream together, then add egg and molasses.
Mix thoroughly.
Add all this to dry mixture and blend well.
Form teaspoons of dough and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until they crack and are browned slightly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside (I microwave).
In large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion. In small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until well blended.
Spoon over broccoli mixture; toss to coat. Sprinkle bacon over salad and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot 2 1/2 to 3 hours on high.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.

Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add lasagna to 6 quarts salted boiling water, stirring almost constantly to prevent sticking together, and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix eggs and Ricotta.
Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers, alternating with layers of sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta, until lasagna is all used.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 20 minutes or until Mozzarella cheese is melted.

title: mawmaw's old fashioned applesauce stack cake
directions: Add water to dried apples.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours or until apples are tender.
When apples are consistency you desire for cake, add sugar.
Add spices as desired.
Set aside.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix pork, ham, eggs, milk and bread crumbs together.
Shape into loaf.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard together. Pour over loaf.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Cover with foil and continually baste.

title: oven fried cauliflower
directions: In a heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bag, combine mayonnaise and cauliflower. Close and shake to coat. Add breadcrumbs. Close and shake to coat. Spread in a single layer on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: lesley's buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls; chill. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler and keep warm.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Let cool on waxed paper.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Place together all the above ingredients in blender on high speed for 15 seconds, stirring top enough to blend with a bowl scraper.
Add 3/4 cup more salad oil very slowly, blending with scraper.
This should take about 30 seconds.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Place chicken in pan, meaty side up.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; place chicken breasts, tomatoes and mushrooms in a 9x13 baking dish.
Combine dressing, soup mix, oregano and bay leaves.
Pour sauce over chicken and vegetables. Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler and cool.
When marshmallow/milk is cool, add salt and almond.
Fold in heavy cream, whipped.
Spread 1/3 of mixture in the pie shell.
Top with 6 fresh peaches, sliced.
If peaches are tart, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Chill several hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: You may add black olives and green peppers.
Cook vermicelli; drain; mix all ingredients and chill well.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift
together	flour, soda, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon
and
salt.
The
dry
mixture is added to the other ingredients and beat together for about 4 minutes.	Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
