Makes one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans using package directions; drain.
Combine lima beans, soup, pimentos and melted butter in 2-quart casserole; mix well.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with electric beater on lowest speed about 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake at once. Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter or margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, flour, salt, baking powder, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake.

title: bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, except bacon and cheese. Remove from blender and heat with cheese. Serve topped with crumbled bacon. Serves 8.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add more water if stew becomes too thick.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix oil and sugar together, then add beaten eggs.
Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Batter will be fairly stiff.
Then fold in nuts and carrots.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven approximately 55 to 60 minutes.
(May take a little longer.)
Test with a toothpick for doneness.

title: 3-2-1 cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except milk and baking powder; remove 1 cup of mixture to be used later.
Mix remaining dough with milk and baking powder (may use less milk).
Dough should be moist but thick.
Spread dough in 2 greased round pans or 1 oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over each pan of dough.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1 1/2-inch balls. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Drain fat.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan. Mix Bisquick and corn well. Roll out and cut into strips (small). Dip into butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce; arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna.
Top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagna pieces into cheese mixture below.
End with a final layer of lasagna; pour remaining sauce over, making sure all lasagna pieces are covered with sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
(Don't be concerned with empty space at ends of the pan.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand 15 minutes; cut in squares to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In saucepan with steamer basket, steam zucchini over boiling water until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook. Meanwhile in mixing bowl, combine melted butter and stuffing mix. Spread half of mixture over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In another bowl, combine zucchini, carrots, onion, soup and sour cream.
Spoon vegetable mixture over stuffing in baking pan.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saucepan scotchies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in vanilla, flour and baking powder; stir until smooth.
Add nuts; mix lightly.
Smooth batter in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake!

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Put Oreo cookies in a plastic bag.
Roll with rolling pin. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Press crumbs down tightly. Melt margarine, then melt chocolate in with margarine.
Beat eggs well.
Put in chocolate mixture.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on medium heat until eggs are mixed well.
Remove from heat; add powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread over Oreo crust.
Chill about 30 minutes. Spread softened ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip and more crushed Oreo cookies.
Keep in freezer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: california cake
directions: In a large bowl, add yellow cake mix, lemon Jell-O and 3/4 cup water; mix well.
Add eggs and cooking oil; mix well.
Bake in a greased oblong pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, mix together powdered sugar and juice from lemons.
Remove cake from oven and while still warm, make holes with fork over every inch of cake, going about half way down.
Pour lemon and powdered sugar glaze over top and let stand.
Spread any remaining glaze over top of cake.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet until soft.
Stir in ground beef and brown well.
Drain grease.
Stir in peas, rice and tomatoes.
Place in 2-quart casserole and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream and meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix together.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a large skillet, saute meat balls, half at the time, in hot butter.
Remove meat balls.
Gradually stir in 1 cup of water and bouillon cube.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Return meat balls to skillet. Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and evaporated milk together and cook uncovered 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let set until hard.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together. Add milk and vanilla. Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Alternate with flour. Beat well after each addition.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise approximately 1/4-inch thick or less.
Arrange slices in baking dish for top of range; pour sugar over top.
Add stick of butter on top; does not need to be cut up.
Add water.
Put top on dish and cook on top of range at medium until it boils, then turn down to low; cook until syrup becomes thick and potatoes are tender (stick ice pick through potatoes to see if tender).
If syrup becomes too thick, add a small amount of water and continue to cook until done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: granny's broccoli-cheese muffins
directions: Mix all together and bake in mini muffin pans at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili potato
directions: In a non-stick skillet, saute onions. Add the chili & cheese. Heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly. Pour over baked potatoes & serve.

title: chocolate cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a bundt pan.
Cream together the butter, cream cheese, and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the all-purpose flour, self-rising flour, and cocoa.

Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the whipping cream. Add the vanilla extract and mix well. Stir in walnuts. Pour into the prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately and cool before slicing.

title: poppy's ranch beans
directions: In crock-pot, add water and salt.
Add beans and bacon; cook until beans soften.
Add barbecue sauce; cook until beans are done.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Place onion in skillet; add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar. Cook 20 minutes covered.
Add onion mixture to combined beans. Add crumbled bacon.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: take-home cranberry relish
directions: Wash fruit.
Peel apples and oranges.
Cut into small pieces. Put fruit into blender or food processor and blend.
Pour into bowl and add sugar.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn chowder soup
directions: In large kettle, cook bacon to crisp.
Remove bacon.
Pour off fat, except for 3 tablespoons.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes, covered. Add corn and milk.
Heat well.
Season.
Add bacon.
Serve with parsley and paprika.

title: joyce's rotel squash
directions: Cook in medium size saucepan on medium heat the squash, onion, salt, pepper, butter and water until vegetables are tender; drain. Add Ro-Tel and bread crumbs.
Pour mixture into a quart casserole dish.
Top with Velveeta slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serve at once.

title: herbed seasoned potatoes
directions: In saucepan, cover potatoes and onions with water.
Simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid. Transfer potatoes and onions to large bowl.
In saucepan, combine potato liquid, parsley, flour and thyme.
Simmer until smooth and slightly thickened.
Reduce heat; add egg, stirring constantly until mixture becomes light yellow in color.
Season with pepper. Pour sauce over potatoes and mix well.
Makes 12 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: egg salad miniatures
directions: Combine eggs, olives and onion; blend in mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread bread rounds (or other shapes) with egg mixture. Garnish with sliced olive or tiny stars cut from jelled cranberry sauce.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Sliver chicken.
Make chicken gravy mix as directed, except use asparagus juice for 1/4 of the liquid.
To chicken gravy, add lemon pepper, sherry, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add mayonnaise and stir until well blended.
Make crepes by favorite recipe.
To a crepe, add a little slivered chicken, a stalk or two of asparagus and 1 tablespoon gravy mix.
Fold crepe over and lay in long baking dish.
Pour remaining gravy over crepes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and run under broiler in oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide all ingredients in half.
Crumble on half of sheet cake into the bottom of a punch bowl.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour half (1 package) over cake.
Layer pie filling, pineapple, coconut and Cool Whip in that order.
Repeat layers, beginning with cake again and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served.

title: grandma's m&m's cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugars, vanilla, water and egg well. Add the flour and salt.
Blend well.
Add M&M's last.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Saute shallots in butter in small saucepan. Add flour and herbs; cook and stir until mixture bubbles and thickens. Gradually add water; stir in blueberries.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: my favorite microwave cake
directions: Grease microwave tube pan and coat with cinnamon and sugar. Cook 10 minutes on Low power and 5 minutes on High power (depending on microwave).
Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared microwave tube pan.
Invert on cake dish and cool, then slip pan off.
Yum, yum.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over cucumber mixture. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Keeps well, like pickles.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet, heat oil till hot. Cook steak and onions till almost done. Add green peppers, cook 4-5 min. more. Stir broth mixture, add to steak. Reduce heat, cook till sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: jamaica orange amaretto biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a baking sheet.
Sift first 3 ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center; add the remaining ingredients.
By hand, work this into the dry mixture until a dough is formed.
Divide dough in half.
On the baking sheet, shape each half into a flat strip, 1 inch high and 2 1/2 inches wide.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly, then cut into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Put slices, cut side down, on baking sheet.
Return to oven for 15 minutes to brown.
Remove from oven; lightly sprinkle Jamaican Orange Duster over the top.

title: confetti fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt white chocolate with Eagle Brand milk. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Cool and eat.

title: sausage, peppers and onions with vinegar
directions: Slice sausage into 1/4 inch slices and brown in 2 Tbsp. of the oil in a large heavy skillet, turning occasionally 8-10 minutes. Meanwhile, saut onion, red pepper and garlic in remaining oil in separate skillet until vegetables are slightly wilted.
Stir in vinegar, tomato, salt and oregano.
Remove sausages with slotted spoon from skillet letting fat drain; add to tomato mixture.
Cook covered over medium heat for 15 minutes.

Uncover skillet; cook, stirring occasionally until vegetables are cooked through and vegetable mixture has thickened slightly, about 15 minutes more. Stir in parsley, basil, pepper and a little more salt, if needed. Add a few drops more vinegar if you wish.
Serve with lots of warm French bread and a green salad.
Can serve with rice also.
This may be made ahead, refrigerated and re-heated.
Serves about 6.

title: popcorn or apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Serve the "caramel" dip with the apples or popcorn.

title: sausage pilau
directions: Brown sausage in butter.
Take out sausage, saute onions and bell pepper.
Take out onions and bell pepper, then brown tomato sauce until thick, then add rice, water and other ingredients. Cook until rice is done.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in large mixing bowl.
Boil oleo, shortening, cocoa, salt and water.
Bring to rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and soda mixture, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased 16 x 11 x 1-inch pan (cookie pan) and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° to 350° until done and nicely brown. Makes about 125 balls.

title: spring breeze cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust and chill 4 hours.

title: rhubarb custard pie(makes 2 deep pies)
directions: Mix all the above.
Put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with egg whites, beaten with sugar and cream of tartar.
Put back in the oven for the last 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bones.
Cut up in large pieces and mix with sour cream and soup that have been combined.
Put into a casserole.
Make topping of the cracker crumbs and melted oleo. Spread on top of chicken and cover with poppy seed.
Be sure crumbs are well covered.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
May be served alone or on top of rice or noodles.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cook chocolate and milk together until thick and smooth; let completely cool.
Then add beaten egg yolks, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold into the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.
Frost if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar.
Mix in shortening. Break eggs into measuring cup and fill with milk to measure 1 cup. Pour into mixture and beat vigorously.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute peppers and onion in shortening.
Stir continuously while adding tomatoes; cook five minutes.
Add green chilies, salt, chili powder and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortillas or corn chips. May be made ahead of time and reheated for serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all together to form a ball.
Can sprinkle with crushed nuts or parsley.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Mix oil, orange juice, salt and cornstarch.
Heat on High. Add all vegetables.
Stirring, turn heat on medium.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: seafood and noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter in	saucepan.
Blend
in
flour,
salt
and pepper.
Add
milk gradually, stirring constantly.	Cook until sauce is thickened.
Place	a bed of cooked noodles in greased casserole dish.
Add shrimp
and
crab meat on top of noodles. Cover with above
cream
sauce.
Sprinkle
cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Pour
melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate 350° oven until sauce is bubbly and crumbs are golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, cool, peel and slice in cubes.
Put in a large bowl.
Fry bacon until crispy; drain on towels.
Leave grease.
Cut up onion; fry in grease.
Spoon on top of potatoes. Also, put parsley, sugar, salt and pepper over potatoes.
In grease, add vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Mix gently.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine and beat stiff.

title: mexican vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss kidney beans, corn, olives, green onions, green pepper and onion; set aside.

title: three-village inn apple crisp
directions: Cover the bottom of an 8-inch square pan, to a depth of 2-inches, with apples.
Mix together rest of the ingredients and sprinkle on top of the apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix the other ingredients well.
Pour over the crackers and mix with hands. When totally coated, put on a cookie sheet to dry.
Store in a tin.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread 1/2 of package of chipped beef in casserole bottom. Wrap 2 slices bacon around each breast and place in casserole. Use rest of chipped beef on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then take out of oven and pour cream of chicken soup over top. Bake 30 minutes more.
Serve over seasoned cooked rice.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add yeast mixture and oil to dry ingredients.
Cut and bake at 400° until brown.
Dough may be refrigerated for up to 3 days.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 225°.
Put butter on jelly roll pan and let melt. In small bowl, mix sugar and spices.
In larger bowl, beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add nuts and toss until coated well.
Add sugar/spice mixture and toss again.
Spread out on jelly roll pan and bake 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: pineapple ham pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse.
Place in large bowl.
Add peas, ham, pineapple and celery.
Over low heat, warm vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves; cool.
Pour over ham mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 4 cups.

title: venison steaks in red wine roux
directions: In a large frying pan, cook the venison medallions with the onion in 1 Tbsp. butter until the medallions are done.
Remove the venison and keep it warm in the oven.
Add mushrooms and gravy mix (using red wine instead of water) to the pan.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Make the red potatoes, and mash with the cream, butter and paprika.
To serve, add the medallions to the sauce and pour over the mashed potatoes.
Serves 6-8.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and jam.
Fold marshmallow cream into mixture.
Chill to serve with fresh fruit, cookies or as a topping for pound cake.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Keep cheese at room temperature and beat until soft.
Add condensed milk to cheese and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and melted chips; beat.
Add vanilla.
Pour on crust (make crust with crumbs, butter and sugar; press in a greased 9-inch spring-form pan).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: lemon lift punch
directions: Freeze all but Sprite; set out to thaw approximately 3 hours before serving.
Thaw to slush stage.
Add Sprite.
Yield:
40 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt shortening in water over high heat.
Add sifted flour, stirring rapidly until thickened.
Put mixture in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 40 minutes in oven set at 400°.
Let set in oven 10 minutes after heat is turned off.
Remove and slit to let moisture escape.
Do not put in plastic bag.
Serve with ice cream and hot fudge.
Makes 12.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box except use milk instead of water. Let cool, then split layers.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Put between layers and put icing on top.

title: glazed pineapple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two crust pie using 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle coconut over bottom of pie crust lined pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, mix ground beef and onion.
Cook until beef is browned; drain.
In large bowl, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add beef mixture and noodles; mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bother salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients, including dry gelatin. No bother; it's all done.

title: kansas city steak soup
directions: Melt butter in a 4-quart pan.
Add flour; stir until smooth. Add 2 cups water and stir.
Saute steak in pan; add to mixture. Preboil onion, carrot and celery in remaining 2 cups water; add to soup.
Add all other ingredients to soup.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 12 servings. Steak soup is considered "the" soup in Kansas City!

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in butter, egg and vanilla.
Blend and drop by 1/2 teaspoon at least 2-inches apart on heavy foil on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown (7 minutes).
Cool, then remove.
Store with wax paper between layers.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased 9-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: goof balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.

title: chow mein crispies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add noodles.
Drop onto wax paper and cool.

title: bacon and cabbage soup
directions: In a large pan (stock pot), saute bacon until cooked through and crisp.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender.
Add stock and cook until hot.
Drain and rinse beans.
Add to mixture.
Add cabbage and cook until cabbage is tender.
Add sage and cayenne to taste.

title: abondiga soup
directions: Roll beef into meatballs.
Put meatballs into a pot and add enough water to just cover meatballs.
Boil until done.
Empty water and add new water, filling to middle of the pot.
Add celery, onion and tomato sauce to meatballs and water.
Boil until celery is done.
Add spices.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: broiled tomatoes with sour cream topping
directions: Mix ingredients except tomatoes.
Top tomatoes with mixture. Place under broiler until light brown.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and salt.
Cut and wash chicken; drain.
Arrange chicken pieces in baking pan and pour oil and lemon mixture over it.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, basting once.
Remove cover; baste and bake 30 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter no-bakes
directions: Bring to boil in large saucepan, margarine, sugar and milk. Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper; let harden.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over layers. Cover and chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shirley's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and chill.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Brown in a heavy skillet the bacon, cut into 2-inch pieces. Add and cook until well blended the vinegar, sugar, mustard, flour and salt.
Add and heat until steaming well.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour the potatoes and onions.
Add frankfurters 20 minutes before cooking is finished.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat the cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in all ingredients, except nuts.
Chill several hours, covered.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts to coat.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick and easy pizza
directions: Take 1 English muffin; cut in half to have 2 slices.
Spread Ragu or other brand of spaghetti sauce on each (about 2 tablespoons each).
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese to taste.
Add extra pizza toppings (cooked hamburger, pepperoni, green onion, etc.).
Place on foil and place in broiler until cheese is melted (3 to 5 minutes).

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Scrape bottom of bowl occasionally.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan and place in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
When finished, put shaved chocolate over top of it.
When cool, refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet; add dry rice and arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over the chicken and add water.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Sometimes, you may need to add more water.

title: lower fat pesto
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine basil, spinach, cheese, nuts, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover. Blend or process with several on/off turns until a paste forms. Scrape sides several times and blend well.
With machine running, slowly add the oil and 2 tablespoons water and blend until reaches consistency of soft butter.
Transfer to storage container, cover and refrigerate up to 2 days or freeze up to one month.
Makes 3/4 cup.
Contains 29 calories, 2 grams fat and 2 milligrams cholesterol.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Microwave margarine; add onion and garlic.
Microwave 3 minutes until onion is soft.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute more. Gradually stir in milk 1/4 teaspoon pepper and salt.
Microwave 10 minutes until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Combine cheese, egg and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in carrots, zucchini, broccoli and spinach.
Layer pan, 1/4 onion sauce, 1/3 noodles, 1/2 vegetable mixture.
Repeat. Top with onion sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes if browning too fast; cover with foil.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Steam or slightly brown celery and onion in butter; add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer all for 5 minutes.
Put in buttered casserole topped with nuts and noodles.
Heat in oven at 350°.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Brown ground beef, then add other ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Fix rice according to package directions.
Pour hamburger mixture over rice.

title: baked dried corn
directions: Soak corn in two cups hot milk for one hour.
Add cold milk, eggs, sugar, salt, butter and pepper.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend until fine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash enough strawberries to make 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil about 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops of food color.
Cool.

title: hot fruity cider
directions: Slice orange into thin slices.
Pour cider into 2-quart crock-pot.
Drop in cinnamon sticks and orange slices.
Heat on low setting.
Serve when hot.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions; mix together sour cream and cream cheese with sugar and small amount of juice from canned fruit.
Layer in punch bowl:
cake (crumbled), fruit, pudding and cream cheese mixture (three times).
Seal
with pie filling; then seal with Cool Whip and top with fruit.

title: black beans
directions: Drain beans and add all ingredients.
Simmer until tender, about 2 hours.
Stir in 2 cups Monterey Jack cheese.
Eat as a main dish, plain or over rice.
Good served with Chicken Salad Burritos, also.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cooled cornbread in oblong pan.
Layer vegetables. Mix well.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice as a dressing; pour over salad.
Top with cheese.
For a moist salad, prepare more dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: You will need 1 (9-inch) pie tin.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and make into bite size balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: colored ice cubes
directions: Get any ice tray and fill it up with Kool-Aid.
Put it in the freezer for 1 hour and 30 minutes, then you will have a nice, cool snack.

title: pampered beef fillets
directions: In saucepan, combine chopped mushrooms, onion and 1/2 cup of water; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir Burgundy, salt and dash of pepper. Place in plastic bag.
Pour in wine sauce.
Fasten bag securely. Marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Remove fillets, reserving sauce.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 7 minutes.
Turn and broil 6 minutes.
Top with mushroom crowns (X-shape in top) last few minutes of broiling.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley. Heat sauce and serve.

title: madeira cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a well-greased Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.
Let cool, turn out of pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and poppy seed.

title: limeade-raspberry drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Blend.
May serve over ice cubes.
Makes 25 (4 ounce) servings.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove from pan and crumble when cooled. In bacon fat, fry onion and green pepper until soft. Drain beans. In casserole dish, mix together beans, bacon and onion/green peppers. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients until smooth, then pour over the bean mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sissy's cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions, except add four eggs. While cake is baking, cook strawberries, adding sugar.
While cake is hot, punch holes into it with a fork and pour hot strawberries over cake.
Let cake cool.

title: hot wings
directions: Cook frozen wings in a 350° oven for 30 minutes on a baking sheet.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Stir in hot sauce.
Add chicken wings. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes to coat them well with sauce.
Makes 3 servings.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch dish, layer bread on bottom.
Sprinkle on cheese over bread.
Mix eggs and milk with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the bread and cheese.
End with bacon crumbs sprinkled on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cantonese beef
directions: Brown beef in oil in large skillet, 5 minutes.
Combine water and gravy mix.
Add to beef with red pepper, water chestnuts, scallions, soy sauce and ginger.
Bring to a full boil.

title: frito salad
directions: Pour dressing over all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serve over Fritos chips.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and heat; do not boil. Serve hot.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Divide the package of crumbs in 2 equal parts, sprinkling 1/2 of the crumbs on bottom of buttered dish. Add squash mixture and use remaining crumbs on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: raspberry pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla.
Cut together.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans; set aside 3/4 cup mixture.
Press remaining crumbs in 9-inch square baking pan. Spread preserves over crumb mixture; sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans and reserved mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until crumb is lightly brown and preserves are bubbly.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fried mozzarella cheese
directions: Cut
the cheese into 36 (2/3 inch) cubes.
Dredge cubes in flour, dip in egg, then roll in crumbs.
Press crumbs onto cubes lightly, then again, dip in egg and roll in crumbs.
Let breaded cubes dry on a rack at room temperature 1/2 hour.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar, melted butter and baking powder. Then add 1 egg and 1/2 cup milk. Top with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon. Put in hot oven. You can double this.

title: chicken with olives and capers
directions: Place pieces of chicken in oven pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper. In a bowl, put minced garlic, olive oil, wine, capers and olives, mixing well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° until tender.
Keep basting with mixture that's in the pan.
Add water as needed.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes (do not overbake). Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set (1 minute).
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into a large pan.
Heat thoroughly and spread into casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with thin slices of cheese.
Sprinkle bacon bits over cheese and top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine all the ingredients and serve in punch cups.
Makes 15 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add 1/2 of the milk and flour; mix well, then add the remaining milk and flour and mix well.
Add the baking powder and flavorings.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare 3 flavors of jello separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor in 8-inch loaf pan and gel overnight.
Combine lemon jello, sugar and remaining 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened; add Cool Whip to lemon jello and mix carefully.
Cut the firm jello flavors into 1-inch squares and add to lemon jello and Cool Whip.
Mix carefully.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: cookies -n- cream pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl. Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute. Let stand 5 minutes, then fold in whipped topping and crushed cookies. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes before serving. Store leftovers in freezer.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except 2 slices of bacon and half of the olives.
Chill and garnish with the remaining bacon and olives.

title: potato bisque
directions: In a large kettle, melt margarine over medium heat; add onion and celery and cook until limp, stirring occasionally, approximately 10 minutes.
Add potatoes; brown and cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and broth.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk and heat until ready to boil.
Add cornstarch mix.
Continue cooking until thick.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Put vegetables and meat mixture in large pan with 4 cups water.
Cook about 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Mix flour and water to make a paste.
Stir in mixture to thicken.
Add peas.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve over biscuits.

title: marie's lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain off grease.
Add onion, pepper, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, reserved tomato juice and mushrooms.
Cook on medium heat, stirring frequently, until liquid is evaporated and vegetables are tender.
Butter bottom of casserole dish.

title: rotel dip
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes together in a heavy saucepan over medium heat until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coleslaw for freezing
directions: Mix together cabbage and salt; let stand one hour, then squeeze out excess moisture.
Add carrot and pepper.
Bring remaining ingredients for the dressing to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over slaw mixture and mix gently.
Pack into freezer containers in meal size portions; cover and freeze.
This salad thaws quickly and will re-freeze.
Stays crisp.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into strips about 1/4-inch thick and 1/2-inch wide. Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Marinate meat in ingredients for 24 hours in a covered container, stirring at least once in the first 8 hours.
Place meat on rack in oven (125° to 150°) and dry 6 to 8 hours.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let margarine and grated cheese come to room temperature, then mix.
Add flour and onion soup mix.
Mix together and divide into 4 pieces.
Roll each one in foil and freeze.
Slice thin and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Shred ham; soften cream cheese.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 package of Ranch dressing to ham and softened cream cheese.

title: crispy baked snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate pepper on fish and arrange on baking sheet.
Melt butter.
Add onion and saute on low heat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture on fish fillets and bake until fish flakes easily and topping is golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.
Serves 6 people.
